{"type":"text","timestamp":1778699160316,"sessionID":"ses_1dd453a87ffea8uOW3O9LERgqm","part":{"id":"prt_e22bb4a43002t0PMnZJzKEBpoE","messageID":"msg_e22bafc30001PK5oIkEYj8bMCg","sessionID":"ses_1dd453a87ffea8uOW3O9LERgqm","type":"text","text":"The log shows the only large successful micro-opt was isolating the multiply datapath; later attempts that added gating to divider/control/forwarding or changed metadata regressed. I’m choosing a smaller local ALU cleanup: isolate shift hardware inputs for non-shift ops without changing pipeline or control behavior.","time":{"start":1778699160131,"end":1778699160315},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0a6c4d613f17c5df016a04cb97fd94819ba2f6f85412b5ea23","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778699175308,"sessionID":"ses_1dd453a87ffea8uOW3O9LERgqm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_Ci485rkKQcymEiVlqIWS1XFo","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r11s0\n+title: Gate shift operand path\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best result came from a narrow ALU cleanup that kept the pipeline unchanged while reducing always-live arithmetic hardware around common RV32I operations. Most later attempts regressed when they added control/state, altered forwarding, or rewrote divider and branch paths. The remaining safer micro-opt target is the ALU shift cone: SLL/SRL/SRA are relatively infrequent in CoreMark, but the live shifter still shares the EX result mux and operand routing with adds, compares, branches, and memory address generation.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Refactor rtl/alu.sv so shift operations use a small is_shift_op predicate and gated shift operands. Feed the real a operand and b[4:0] shamt only for ALU_SLL, ALU_SRL, and ALU_SRA; otherwise drive the shifter inputs with constants and use those gated wires in the existing shift case arms. Keep all ALU op encodings, RV32M behavior, RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitutions, and single-cycle pipeline timing unchanged.\n+\n+  This should reduce switching, LUT input pressure, and routing from the barrel-shift cone into the common EX-stage ALU result path without adding any new state, stalls, predictor metadata, memory behavior, or RVFI-visible changes. The expected upside is modest but it follows the one proven pattern for this core: isolate a rarely used ALU sub-datapath while preserving the successful five-stage timing model.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Add is_shift_op gating for SLL/SRL/SRA operands and use gated shift wires in the existing ALU case while preserving RV32IM and ALTOPS semantics.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Retain or extend shift-operation vectors for SLL, SRL, and SRA edge cases after the ALU shift-path refactor.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r11s0\n+title: Gate shift operand path\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best result came from a narrow ALU cleanup that kept the pipeline unchanged while reducing always-live arithmetic hardware around common RV32I operations. Most later attempts regressed when they added control/state, altered forwarding, or rewrote divider and branch paths. The remaining safer micro-opt target is the ALU shift cone: SLL/SRL/SRA are relatively infrequent in CoreMark, but the live shifter still shares the EX result mux and operand routing with adds, compares, branches, and memory address generation.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Refactor rtl/alu.sv so shift operations use a small is_shift_op predicate and gated shift operands. Feed the real a operand and b[4:0] shamt only for ALU_SLL, ALU_SRL, and ALU_SRA; otherwise drive the shifter inputs with constants and use those gated wires in the existing shift case arms. Keep all ALU op encodings, RV32M behavior, RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitutions, and single-cycle pipeline timing unchanged.\n+\n+  This should reduce switching, LUT input pressure, and routing from the barrel-shift cone into the common EX-stage ALU result path without adding any new state, stalls, predictor metadata, memory behavior, or RVFI-visible changes. The expected upside is modest but it follows the one proven pattern for this core: isolate a rarely used ALU sub-datapath while preserving the successful five-stage timing model.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Add is_shift_op gating for SLL/SRL/SRA operands and use gated shift wires in the existing ALU case while preserving RV32IM and ALTOPS semantics.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Retain or extend shift-operation vectors for SLL, SRL, and SRA edge cases after the ALU shift-path refactor.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r11s0\n+title: Gate shift operand path\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best result came from a narrow ALU cleanup that kept the pipeline unchanged while reducing always-live arithmetic hardware around common RV32I operations. Most later attempts regressed when they added control/state, altered forwarding, or rewrote divider and branch paths. The remaining safer micro-opt target is the ALU shift cone: SLL/SRL/SRA are relatively infrequent in CoreMark, but the live shifter still shares the EX result mux and operand routing with adds, compares, branches, and memory address generation.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Refactor rtl/alu.sv so shift operations use a small is_shift_op predicate and gated shift operands. Feed the real a operand and b[4:0] shamt only for ALU_SLL, ALU_SRL, and ALU_SRA; otherwise drive the shifter inputs with constants and use those gated wires in the existing shift case arms. Keep all ALU op encodings, RV32M behavior, RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitutions, and single-cycle pipeline timing unchanged.\n+\n+  This should reduce switching, LUT input pressure, and routing from the barrel-shift cone into the common EX-stage ALU result path without adding any new state, stalls, predictor metadata, memory behavior, or RVFI-visible changes. The expected upside is modest but it follows the one proven pattern for this core: isolate a rarely used ALU sub-datapath while preserving the successful five-stage timing model.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Add is_shift_op gating for SLL/SRL/SRA operands and use gated shift wires in the existing ALU case while preserving RV32IM and ALTOPS semantics.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Retain or extend shift-operation vectors for SLL, SRL, and SRA edge cases after the ALU shift-path refactor.\"\n","additions":17,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778699175304,"end":1778699175308}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a6c4d613f17c5df016a04cb9835d4819bb6149eefe13ccf59"}},"id":"prt_e22bb4aff001fExdr2EZbI5FhV","sessionID":"ses_1dd453a87ffea8uOW3O9LERgqm","messageID":"msg_e22bafc