{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778699183361,"sessionID":"ses_1dd453a87ffea8uOW3O9LERgqm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_k9wjORzVfftt6MesTVQOeuSw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260513-001-r11s0\n2: title: Gate shift operand path\n3: category: micro_opt\n4: motivation: |\n5:   The current best result came from a narrow ALU cleanup that kept the pipeline unchanged while reducing always-live arithmetic hardware around common RV32I operations. Most later attempts regressed when they added control/state, altered forwarding, or rewrote divider and branch paths. The remaining safer micro-opt target is the ALU shift cone: SLL/SRL/SRA are relatively infrequent in CoreMark, but the live shifter still shares the EX result mux and operand routing with adds, compares, branches, and memory address generation.\n6: hypothesis: |\n7:   Refactor rtl/alu.sv so shift operations use a small is_shift_op predicate and gated shift operands. Feed the real a operand and b[4:0] shamt only for ALU_SLL, ALU_SRL, and ALU_SRA; otherwise drive the shifter inputs with constants and use those gated wires in the existing shift case arms. Keep all ALU op encodings, RV32M behavior, RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitutions, and single-cycle pipeline timing unchanged.\n8: \n9:   This should reduce switching, LUT input pressure, and routing from the barrel-shift cone into the common EX-stage ALU result path without adding any new state, stalls, predictor metadata, memory behavior, or RVFI-visible changes. The expected upside is modest but it follows the one proven pattern for this core: isolate a rarely used ALU sub-datapath while preserving the successful five-stage timing model.\n10: expected_impact:\n11:   fitness_delta_pct: 2\n12:   confidence: medium\n13: changes:\n14:   - file: rtl/alu.sv\n15:     description: \"Add is_shift_op gating for SLL/SRL/SRA operands and use gated shift wires in the existing ALU case while preserving RV32IM and ALTOPS semantics.\"\n16:   - file: test/test_alu.py\n17:     description: \"Retain or extend shift-operation vectors for SLL, SRL, and SRA edge cases after the ALU shift-path refactor.\"\n\n(End of file - total 17 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260513-001-r11s0\ntitle: Gate shift operand path\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The current best result came from a narrow ALU cleanup that kept the pipeline unchanged while reducing always-live arithmetic hardware around common RV32I operations. Most later attempts regressed when they added control/state, altered forwarding, or rewrote divider and branch paths. The remaining safer micro-opt target is the ALU shift cone: SLL/SRL/SRA are relatively infrequent in CoreMark, but the live shifter still shares the EX result mux and operand routing with adds, compares, branches, and memory address generation.\nhypothesis: |\n  Refactor rtl/alu.sv so shift operations use a small is_shift_op predicate and gated shift operands. Feed the real a operand and b[4:0] shamt only for ALU_SLL, ALU_SRL, and ALU_SRA; otherwise drive the shifter inputs with constants and use those gated wires in the existing shift case arms. Keep all ALU op encodings, RV32M behavior, RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitutions, and single-cycle pipeline timing unchanged.\n\n  This should reduce switching, LUT input pressure, and routing from the barrel-shift cone into the common EX-stage ALU result path without adding any new state, stalls, predictor metadata, memory behavior, or RVFI-visible changes. The expected upside is modest but it follows the one proven pattern for this core: isolate a rarely used ALU sub-datapath while preserving the successful five-stage timing model.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n    description: \"Add is_shift_op gating for SLL/SRL/SRA operands and use gated shift wires in the existing ALU case while preserving RV32IM and ALTOPS semantics.\"\n  - file: test/test_alu.py\n    description: \"Retain or extend shift-operation vectors for SLL, SRL, and SRA edge cases after the ALU shift-path refactor.\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778699183357,"end":1778699183360}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08937238a2de4176016a04cbaee53c819bbb8d84ff8572c00d"}},"id":"prt_e22bba39d001dfpa8AEsTfqaBo","sessionID":"ses_1dd453a87ffea8uOW3O9LERgqm","messageID":"msg_e22bb85f7001sbB2IzhHJJuA6h"}}
