{"type":"text","timestamp":1778700925712,"sessionID":"ses_1dd2a5685ffemZ77M67VroBydU","part":{"id":"prt_e22d636a10012OoMW3MmgszJnB","messageID":"msg_e22d5d727001BBI6LLXDT5Agjx","sessionID":"ses_1dd2a5685ffemZ77M67VroBydU","type":"text","text":"The relevant history shows the only strong micro-opt win was isolating a large ALU sub-datapath, while later added gating, predictor/front-end, divider, forwarding, reset, and MEM lane rewrites mostly regressed or broke. I’m going to propose a narrower MEM-path retiming: precompute store byte-lane mask and replicated write data in EX so the MEM stage drives dmem/RVFI store fields from registered values instead of rebuilding them on the memory output path.","time":{"start":1778700924577,"end":1778700925711},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_06a0c99bf751fb5c016a04d27c783c8198a617bdde390b9a87","phase":"commentary"}}}}
