{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778700956676,"sessionID":"ses_1dd2a5685ffemZ77M67VroBydU","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_TZiyBSEGHPQpLmoQMlRx0UI9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r13s0\n+title: \"Register store lane outputs\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The successful bench-core micro-optimizations have been narrow timing cleanups that keep the five-stage pipeline and RVFI contract unchanged. The MEM stage still rebuilds store byte replication and byte masks combinationally from EX/MEM every cycle, and those signals directly drive dmem outputs plus RVFI store fields on a path that also carries load extraction and misalignment gating.\n+\n+  Prior MEM lane extraction and forwarding changes regressed when they altered load-data muxing or added new bypass control. A store-only precompute avoids the load result path and should reduce output-side MEM mux depth for stores without changing stalls, branch policy, arithmetic, or retirement behavior.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add registered store-side metadata to the EX/MEM payload: the replicated store write data and the shifted byte-lane mask computed from the already-available forwarded rs2, mem_width, and ALU effective address in EX. Then simplify rtl/mem_stage.sv so dmem_wdata, dmem_wen, rvfi mem_wdata, and rvfi mem_wmask use those registered values, only gating them off for non-store or misaligned accesses.\n+\n+  This should shorten the MEM-stage store output path by moving the width-dependent replication and mask decode one stage earlier, where the operands are already present and the result is captured in EX/MEM. It preserves single-cycle store semantics, load behavior, misalignment traps, memory stall holds, RVFI ALIGNED_MEM reporting, and the nret=1 top-level interface. The expected gain is modest Fmax improvement with minimal IPC risk because no new stalls or predictor state are introduced.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add EX/MEM fields for registered store byte-mask and replicated store write data while preserving existing RVFI payload fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute store write-data replication and byte-lane mask from forwarded rs2, mem_width, and effective address before capturing EX/MEM.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Drive store dmem outputs and RVFI store fields from the registered EX/MEM store metadata, keeping existing misalignment gating and load extraction unchanged.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r13s0\n+title: \"Register store lane outputs\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The successful bench-core micro-optimizations have been narrow timing cleanups that keep the five-stage pipeline and RVFI contract unchanged. The MEM stage still rebuilds store byte replication and byte masks combinationally from EX/MEM every cycle, and those signals directly drive dmem outputs plus RVFI store fields on a path that also carries load extraction and misalignment gating.\n+\n+  Prior MEM lane ex