{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778701993179,"sessionID":"ses_1dd1aebf5ffeRwYw5wzZrFDViu","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_nEH4XSwtSg5gNh1jTF9r80kw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r14s0\n+title: \"Bypass LUI around ALU\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The successful micro-optimization history for this core favors narrow datapath cleanup over new control, prediction, buffering, or memory-lane restructuring. The current EX stage already carries a decoded is_lui bit through ctrl_t, but LUI still enters the full ALU case as ALU_LUI just to return the immediate operand. That keeps one U-type-only operation in the same result mux and ALU op decode used by CoreMark's common adds, compares, branches, and load/store address calculations.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Route LUI writeback in rtl/ex_stage.sv through the existing final EX/MEM result selection, the same style already used for JAL/JALR link data and AUIPC pc_imm_target, and remove ALU_LUI from rtl/alu.sv's active result case. The decoder can still set ctrl.is_lui and an otherwise harmless ALU op, but LUI's architectural result will be in.imm captured directly into ex_mem.alu_result.\n+\n+  This should slightly shrink the monolithic ALU result case and reduce ALU op decode fanout without adding state, stalls, bypasses, predictor metadata, or any RVFI-visible behavior. It is intentionally smaller than the failed AUIPC cleanup: it does not delete existing metadata or change operand-a routing for all instructions, only moves one already-decoded U-type result out of the common ALU datapath.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use the existing ctrl.is_lui bit to capture in.imm directly into ex_mem.alu_result, alongside the current jump and AUIPC result selection, while preserving pc_next and redirect behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the live ALU_LUI result arm or make it unreachable/harmless so the common ALU case no longer needs to route the LUI immediate through its output mux.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Keep LUI legal with ctrl.is_lui/reg_write/alu_src set, but assign a simple non-special ALU op because EX now handles the LUI result directly.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,19 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r14s0\n+title: \"Bypass LUI around ALU\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The successful micro-optimization history for this core favors narrow datapath cleanup over new control, prediction, buffering, or memory-lane restructuring. The current EX stage already carries a decoded is_lui bit through ctrl_t, but LUI still enters the full ALU case as ALU_LUI just to return the immediate operand. That keeps one U-type-only operation in the same result mux and ALU op decode used by CoreMark's common adds, compares, branches, and load/store address calculations.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Route LUI writeback in rtl/ex_stage.sv through the existing final EX/MEM result selection, the same style already used for JAL/JALR link data and AUIPC pc_imm_target, and remove ALU_LUI from rtl/alu.sv's active result case. The decoder can still set ctrl.is_lui and an otherwise harmless ALU op, but LUI's architectural result will be in.imm captured directly into ex_mem.alu_result.\n+\n+  This should slightly shrink the monolithic ALU result case and reduce ALU op decode fanout without adding state, stalls, bypasses, predictor metadata, or any RVFI-visible behavior. It is intentionally smaller than the failed AUIPC cleanup: it does not delete existing metadata or change operand-a routing for all instructions, only moves one already-decoded U-type result out of the common ALU datapath.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use the existing ctrl.is_lui bit to capture in.imm directly into ex_mem.alu_result, alongside the current jump and AUIPC result selection, while preserving pc_next and redirect behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the live ALU_LUI result arm or make it unreachable/harmless so the common ALU case no longer needs to route the LUI immediate through its output mux.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Keep LUI legal with ctrl.is_lui/reg_write/alu_src set, but assign a simple non-special ALU op because EX now handles the LUI result directly.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bo