{"type":"text","timestamp":1778703058685,"sessionID":"ses_1dd098211ffetSyl7lEBmzYkFB","part":{"id":"prt_e22f6c604001vO0WKTHqs8QbS1","messageID":"msg_e22f6a72f002Of7gj6JRbMC1FU","sessionID":"ses_1dd098211ffetSyl7lEBmzYkFB","type":"text","text":"The history rules out most obvious ALU gating, branch prediction, MEM lane, reset, metadata, and forwarding cleanups. I’m choosing a narrower micro-opt that removes duplicated destination-register compare work by moving forwarding select generation into `ex_stage`, where the same source operands are already muxed, instead of changing dataflow or adding state.","time":{"start":1778703058436,"end":1778703058683},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_094a402509c0b383016a04dad24c988198933bc11b5d18812c","phase":"commentary"}}}}
