{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778703094134,"sessionID":"ses_1dd098211ffetSyl7lEBmzYkFB","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_0FazVJuHbn2IrUWXSlYhJtMo","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r15s0\n+title: \"Fold forwarding into EX\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core computes EX operand bypass selects in a standalone forward_unit, then routes two 2-bit selects plus both destination-register/control bundles across the top level into ex_stage. Prior micro-opts that changed ALU, MEM, branch prediction, or load-use behavior mostly regressed, so the next promising angle is a placement/routing cleanup that preserves the exact five-stage behavior and does not add any datapath cones.\n+\n+  Forwarding is on every ALU, branch, and load/store address cycle, and its compare outputs directly control the EX operand muxes. Keeping the compare and mux logic in one module may let yosys flatten and place the equality checks with the consuming muxes, while also removing top-level select wires from the critical EX operand path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Move the EX/MEM and MEM/WB destination-match logic from rtl/forward_unit.sv into rtl/ex_stage.sv, so ex_stage receives the needed producer metadata and locally chooses rs1 and rs2. Preserve the existing priority order, x0 suppression, load-use behavior, MEM/WB load forwarding, RVFI rs data reporting, and all pipeline registers.\n+\n+  This should be a pure micro-optimization: no new state, no branch or memory policy changes, and no arithmetic rewrite. The expected gain is modest Fmax improvement from giving synthesis a single local cone for destination compare plus operand mux selection and from removing one tiny module boundary/top-level routing detour in the hottest EX input path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Accept EX/MEM and MEM/WB producer metadata directly and generate the rs1/rs2 forwarding selections locally before the existing operand muxes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the standalone forward_unit wiring and connect the existing EX/MEM and MEM/WB rd/reg_write/writeback signals directly to ex_stage.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Delete the now-redundant standalone forwarding module, or leave it unused only if the build file list requires the source to remain present.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r15s0\n+title: \"Fold forwarding into EX\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core computes EX operand bypass selects in a standalone forward_unit, then routes two 2-bit selects plus both destination-register/control bundles across the top level into ex_stage. Prior micro-opts that changed ALU, MEM, branch prediction, or load-use behavior mostly regressed, so the next promising angle is a placement/routing cleanup that preserves the exact five-stage behavior and does not add any datapath cones.\n+\n+  Forwarding is on every ALU, branch, and load/store address cycle, and its compare outputs directly control the EX operand muxes. Keeping the compare and mux logic in one module may let yosys flatten and place the equality checks with the consuming muxes, while also removing top-level select wires from the critical EX operand path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Move the EX/MEM and MEM/WB destination-match logic from rtl/forward_unit.sv into rtl/ex_stage.sv, so ex_stage receives the needed producer metadata and locally chooses rs1 and rs2. Preserve the existing priority order, x0 suppression, load-use behavior, MEM/WB load forwarding, RVFI rs data reporting, and all pipeline registers.\n+\n+  This should be a pure micro-optimization: no new state, no branch or memory policy changes, and no arithmetic rewrite. The expected gain is modest Fmax improvement from giving synthesis a single local cone for destination compare plus operand mux selection and from removing one tiny module boundary/top-level routing detour in the hottest EX input path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Accept EX/MEM and MEM/WB producer metadata directly and generate the rs1/rs2 forwarding selections locally before the existing operand muxes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the standalone forward_unit wiring and connect the existing EX/MEM and MEM/WB rd/reg_write/writeback signals directly to ex_stage.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Delete the now-redundant standalone forwarding module, or leave it unused only if the build file list requires the source to remain present.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001