{"type":"text","timestamp":1778678076345,"sessionID":"ses_1de86d58affeTpiWGgjTyZdKsc","part":{"id":"prt_e21798c90001leRbumGRun9yfv","messageID":"msg_e21795262001YQxagP4Z93f2Sc","sessionID":"ses_1de86d58affeTpiWGgjTyZdKsc","type":"text","text":"No prior bench `micro_opt` attempts exist beyond the baseline retest, so I’m selecting a targeted low-risk optimization: reduce the ALU’s synthesized M-extension cost/critical path by operand-gating and sharing multiplier inputs rather than computing all multiply variants unconditionally.","time":{"start":1778678074512,"end":1778678076344},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0b6b8e531c6347a6016a04793a68d4819b9a1ac9f9349bc16b","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778678091296,"sessionID":"ses_1de86d58affeTpiWGgjTyZdKsc","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_cHJiTlJanJpNm0C0hcnE0XPl","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r1s0\n+title: \"Gate and share M-extension ALU hardware\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current ALU unconditionally forms three independent 64-bit products for every instruction, even though CoreMark is dominated by RV32I arithmetic, branches, and memory traffic. On the Tang Nano 20K this likely burns LUTs and routing and may sit on or near the EX-stage critical path despite M operations being rare in the benchmark.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Refactor rtl/alu.sv so MUL-family operations use a single op-selected signedness/extension path and only feed meaningful operands into the multiplier when the decoded ALU op is an M multiply. Keep the existing RV32M results and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS behavior unchanged, but make non-M ALU operations see simpler combinational logic and give yosys/nextpnr less multiplier-related muxing and routing to optimize through. This is a micro-optimization aimed primarily at improving Fmax and secondarily reducing LUT pressure without changing pipeline timing, RVFI behavior, or architectural state.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Share multiply operand preparation across MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU and gate multiplier inputs for non-multiply ALU ops while preserving exact RV32M and ALTOPS semantics.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Extend or retain M-extension ALU vectors to guard signed, unsigned, and mixed-sign multiply corner cases after the multiplier datapath refactor.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s