ension ALU vectors to guard signed, unsigned, and mixed-sign multiply corner cases after the multiplier datapath refactor.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,15 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r1s0\n+title: \"Gate and share M-extension ALU hardware\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current ALU unconditionally forms three independent 64-bit products for every instruction, even though CoreMark is dominated by RV32I arithmetic, branches, and memory traffic. On the Tang Nano 20K this likely burns LUTs and routing and may sit on or near the EX-stage critical path despite M operations being rare in the benchmark.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Refactor rtl/alu.sv so MUL-family operations use a single op-selected signedness/extension path and only feed meaningful operands into the multiplier when the decoded ALU op is an M multiply. Keep the existing RV32M results and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS behavior unchanged, but make non-M ALU operations see simpler combinational logic and give yosys/nextpnr less multiplier-related muxing and routing to optimize through. This is a micro-optimization aimed primarily at improving Fmax and secondarily reducing LUT pressure without changing pipeline timing, RVFI behavior, or architectural