{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778679187638,"sessionID":"ses_1de762670ffeZQZIpLww8zDwLB","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_5r7bgblE2h5SJB6Zp0mbkB1w","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r2s0\n+title: \"Suppress false load-use stalls\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current hazard unit stalls on any instruction following a load when its\n+  rd matches bits [19:15] or [24:20] of the next instruction. Those bit fields\n+  are not always live source operands: I-type ALU/load/JALR only reads rs1,\n+  stores and branches read both, and U/J/FENCE/EBREAK read neither. False\n+  load-use bubbles directly reduce CoreMark iterations/cycle and become more\n+  expensive under the random instruction/data stall model.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add lightweight source-use qualification to the load-use hazard path so the\n+  pipeline only inserts the one-cycle bubble when the IF/ID instruction will\n+  actually consume the matching source register. Derive rs1_used and rs2_used\n+  combinationally from opcode/funct class in the hazard unit or adjacent decode\n+  wiring, preserving the existing forwarding, RVFI ordering, and memory-stall\n+  behavior. This is a small IPC-focused micro-optimization with low Fmax risk\n+  because it removes unnecessary stalls without changing pipeline depth or the\n+  critical ALU/M-extension datapath.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Qualify load-use detection with source-register usage so rd matches against immediate, U/J, FENCE, or EBREAK bitfields do not stall the pipeline.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Pass the IF/ID instruction opcode context needed for rs1_used/rs2_used qualification into the hazard unit while keeping the nret=1 RVFI interface unchanged.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r2s0\n+title: \"Suppress false load-use stalls\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current hazard unit stalls on any instruction following a load when its\n+  rd matches bits [19:15] or [24:20] of the next instruction. Those bit fields\n+  are not always live source operands: I-type ALU/load/JALR only reads rs1,\n+  stores and branches read both, and U/J/FENCE/EBREAK read neither. False\n+  load-use bubbles directly reduce CoreMark iterations/cycle and become more\n+  expensive under the random instruction/data stall model.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add lightweight source-use qualification to the load-use hazard path so the\n+  pipeline only inserts the one-cycle bubble when the IF/ID instruction will\n+  actually consume the matching source register. Derive rs1_used and rs2_used\n+  combinationally from opcode/funct class in the hazard unit or adjacent decode\n+  wiring, preserving the existing forwarding, RVFI ordering, and memory-stall\n+  behavior. This is a small IPC-focused micro-optimization with low Fmax risk\n+  because it removes unnecessary stalls without changing pipeline depth or the\n+  critical ALU/M-extension datapath.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Qualify load-use detection with source-register usage so rd matches against immediate, U/J, FENCE, or EBREAK bitfields do not stall the pipeline.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Pass the IF/ID instruction opcode context needed for rs1_used/rs2_used qualification into the hazard unit while keeping the nret=1 RVFI interface unchanged.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r2s0\n+title: \"Suppress false load-use stalls\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current hazard unit stalls on any instruction following a load when its\n+  rd matches bits [19:15] or [24:20] of the next instruction. Those bit fields\n+  are not always live source operands: I-type ALU/load/JALR only reads rs1,\n+  stores and branches read both, and U/J/FENCE/EBREAK read neither. False\n+  load-use bubbles directly reduce CoreMark iterations/cycle and become more\n+  expensive under the random instruction/data stall model.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add lightweight source-use qualification to the load-use hazard path so the\n+  pipeline only inserts the one-cycle bubble when the IF/ID instruction will\n+  actually consume the matching source register. Derive rs1_used and rs2_used\n+  combinationally from opcode/funct class in the hazard unit or adjacent decode\n+  wiring, preserving the existing forwarding, RVFI ordering, and memory-stall\n+  behavior. This is a small IPC-focused micro-optimization with low Fmax risk\n+  because it removes unnecessary stalls without changing pipeline depth or the\n+  critical ALU/M-extension datapath.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Qualify load-use detection with source-register usage so rd matches against immediate, U/J, FENCE, or EBREAK bitfields do not stall the pipeline.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Pass the IF/ID instruction opcode context needed for rs1_used/rs2_used qualification into the hazard unit while keeping the nret=1 RVFI interface unchanged.\"\n","additions":27,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778679187633,"end":1778679187637}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0068ad58094de42f016a047d82c584819b8dd08185cc80f95d"}},"id":"prt_e218a4780001InCoX1D6jJ7DhY","sessionID":"ses_1de762670ffeZQZIpLww8zDwLB","messageID":"msg_e218a3aef001w2U7qQ2nZMZOnP"}}
