{"type":"text","timestamp":1778684196026,"sessionID":"ses_1de299b7dffeTEp56YowcVuBua","part":{"id":"prt_e21d6f3eb001qHeuAAb4dOLP97","messageID":"msg_e21d698ae001DuR47RDPxUeLtT","sessionID":"ses_1de299b7dffeTEp56YowcVuBua","type":"text","text":"Prior micro-opts show the best gain came from reducing always-live arithmetic hardware; divider/load-bypass/branch-predict changes regressed by lengthening hot paths or adding stalls. The next low-risk micro-opt is to remove the integer register file reset so synthesis can map it more efficiently instead of forcing 1024 resettable flops/muxes.","time":{"start":1778684195819,"end":1778684196025},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0b36c41ef913ceb8016a049123b07481988757df3535a8f3a4","phase":"commentary"}}}}
