{"type":"text","timestamp":1778686823055,"sessionID":"ses_1de018badffe4BOEQmBkOm5ZkN","part":{"id":"prt_e21ff02bc001IAhiy6E2t4pehb","messageID":"msg_e21fea4d70014VI0uCLfiLHfqD","sessionID":"ses_1de018badffe4BOEQmBkOm5ZkN","type":"text","text":"The prior successful micro-opt was a narrow Fmax win from gating always-live arithmetic; recent regressions came from added stalls, front-end prediction, regfile reset changes, and extra memory control. I’m writing a similarly narrow EX-stage control-transfer datapath gating hypothesis rather than changing pipeline structure or memory behavior.","time":{"start":1778686821052,"end":1778686823054},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_062ef3cbd0309ac4016a049b64d5308199a45089d65f65ad7e","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778686832920,"sessionID":"ses_1de018badffe4BOEQmBkOm5ZkN","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_Upv7lU14JEkV1rb2IX2KIq2N","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r5s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r5s0\n+title: \"Gate EX control-transfer datapath\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage computes branch comparisons, branch targets, and JALR target sums for every instruction, even though CoreMark's hot path is dominated by ordinary ALU and memory operations. Prior results show that narrow gating of always-live datapaths can improve Tang Nano Fmax, while larger structural or predictor changes have repeatedly lost more timing than they recovered in IPC.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Refactor rtl/ex_stage.sv so control-transfer hardware is only active for actual branch or jump instructions. Gate the branch comparator operands when is_branch is false, compute only the selected branch comparison for the decoded branch_op, and feed harmless constants into the branch-target and JALR-target adders when their instruction class is not active. Preserve the existing EX-stage resolution point, misalignment trap behavior, RVFI pc_next reporting, and redirect semantics.\n+\n+  This should reduce EX-stage LUT/routing pressure and remove always-live comparator/adder cones from common RV32I ALU and load/store cycles without adding state, stalls, or front-end prediction metadata. The expected gain is primarily Fmax, with essentially no IPC downside because pipeline timing and retirement behavior remain unchanged.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Gate branch comparator inputs and control-target adders so non-control instructions do not keep branch/jump hardware live on the EX critical path.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r5s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r5s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r5s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r5s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,15 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r5s0\n+title: \"Gate EX control-transfer datapath\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage computes branch comparisons, branch targets, and JALR target sums for every instruction, even though CoreMark's hot path is dominated by ordinary ALU and memory operations. Prior results show that narrow gating of always-live datapaths can improve Tang Nano Fmax, while larger structural or predictor changes have repeatedly lost more timing than they recovered in IPC.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Refactor rtl/ex_stage.sv so control-transfer hardware is only active for actual branch or jump instructions. Gate the branch comparator operands when is_branch is false, compute only the selected branch comparison for the decoded branch_op, and feed harmless constants into the branch-target and JALR-target adders when their instruction class is not active. Preserve the existing EX-stage resolution point, misalignment trap behavior, RVFI pc_next reporting, and redirect semantics.\n+\n+  This should reduce EX-stage LUT/routing pressure and remove always-live comparator/adder cones from common RV32I ALU and load/store cycles without adding state, stalls, or front-end prediction metadata. The expected gain is primarily Fmax, with essentially no IPC downside because pipeline timing and retirement behavior remain unchanged.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Gate branch comparator inputs and control-target adders so non-control instructions do not keep branch/jump hardware live on the EX critical path.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r5s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r5s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r5s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r5s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r5s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,15 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r5s0\n+title: \"Gate EX control-transfer datapath\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage computes branch comparisons, branch targets, and JALR target sums for every instruction, even though CoreMark's hot path is dominated by ordinary ALU and memory operations. Prior results show that narrow gating of always-live datapaths can improve Tang Nano Fmax, while larger structural or predictor changes have repeatedly lost more timing than they recovered in IPC.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Refactor rtl/ex_stage.sv so control-transfer hardware is only active for actual branch or jump instructions. Gate the branch comparator operands when is_branch is false, compute only the selected branch comparison for the decoded branch_op, and feed harmless constants into the branch-target and JALR-target adders when their instruction class is not active. Preserve the existing EX-stage resolution point, misalignment trap behavior, RVFI pc_next reporting, and redirect semantics.\n+\n+  This should reduce EX-stage LUT/routing pressure and remove always-live comparator/adder cones from common RV32I ALU and load/store cycles without adding state, stalls, or front-end prediction metadata. The expected gain is primarily Fmax, with essentially no IPC downside because pipeline timing and retirement behavior remain unchanged.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Gate branch comparator inputs and control-target adders so non-control instructions do not keep branch/jump hardware live on the EX critical path.\"\n","additions":15,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r5s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778686832911,"end":1778686832918}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_062ef3cbd0309ac4016a049b66babc819986e2b9e5ef53002f"}},"id":"prt_e21ff0a9e001b51tl0VjH2HATt","sessionID":"ses_1de018badffe4BOEQmBkOm5ZkN","messageID":"msg_e21fea4d70014VI0uCLfiLHfqD"}}
