{"type":"text","timestamp":1778689237235,"sessionID":"ses_1dddcad38ffeyUtl5MmkF32bVm","part":{"id":"prt_e2223d85b001mwfW2MrSLOVip8","messageID":"msg_e222388430011t86Ax20N9Zxqm","sessionID":"ses_1dddcad38ffeyUtl5MmkF32bVm","type":"text","text":"Prior micro_opt wins came from removing always-live M datapath pressure; the failed divider attempt added normalization/sharing logic. I’m going to propose a narrower divider-input isolation pass that preserves the existing `/` and `%` semantics but gates their operands outside DIV/REM ops, avoiding new pipeline state or altered hazard behavior.","time":{"start":1778689235035,"end":1778689237234},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0a17e18263f5383f016a04a4d2ed308199829f1ebc0ac9682a","phase":"commentary"}}}}
