{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778689265175,"sessionID":"ses_1dddcad38ffeyUtl5MmkF32bVm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_IXoZGjnxTuImZkkqRv2ZEDOU","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r6s0\n+title: Gate divider operands only\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best bench core already benefited strongly from isolating the MUL-family datapath from ordinary RV32I ALU operations. The remaining DIV/REM operators still consume the live ALU operands directly, so yosys may keep wide divider/remainder cones and routing coupled to the EX-stage result mux even when CoreMark is mostly executing adds, compares, loads, stores, and branches.\n+\n+  A prior attempt to share the divider datapath regressed because it introduced signed normalization, restore muxing, and simultaneous quotient/remainder logic. The safer micro-optimization is to avoid that structural rewrite and only gate the raw divider operands outside actual DIV/REM operations.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add an is_divrem_op decode inside rtl/alu.sv and feed the real a/b operands to division and remainder operators only for ALU_DIV, ALU_DIVU, ALU_REM, and ALU_REMU. For all other ALU ops, drive the divider operand wires with harmless constants, then use those gated wires in the existing RV32M divide-by-zero and INT_MIN/-1 cases.\n+\n+  This keeps the pipeline single-cycle, preserves RV32M and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS semantics, and avoids the failed normalization/sharing approach. The expected benefit is primarily Fmax: common RV32I paths should see less divider-related switching, fanout, and routing pressure in the EX ALU result mux without changing IPC, RVFI ordering, memory behavior, or the nret=1 top-level contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Introduce gated div/rem operand wires and use them in the existing DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU case arms while leaving ALTOPS and multiply logic unchanged.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Retain or extend RV32M divide/remainder vectors for divide-by-zero, signed overflow, signed operands, and unsigned corner cases after the operand-gating refactor.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,19 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r6s0\n+title: Gate divider operands only\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best bench core already benefited strongly from isolating the MUL-family datapath from ordinary RV32I ALU operations. The remaining DIV/REM operators still consume the live ALU operands directly, so yosys may keep wide divider/remainder cones and routing coupled to the EX-stage result mux even when CoreMark is mostly executing adds, compares, loads, stores, and branches.\n+\n+  A prior attempt to share the divider datapath regressed because it introduced signed normalization, restore muxing, and simultaneous quotient/remainder logic. The safer micro-optimization is to avoid that structural rewrite and only gate the raw divider operands outside actual DIV/REM operations.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add an is_divrem_op decode inside rtl/alu.sv and feed the real a/b operands to division and remainder operators only for ALU_DIV, ALU_DIVU, ALU_REM, and ALU_REMU. For all other ALU ops, drive the divider operand wires with harmless constants, then use those gated wires in the existing RV32M divide-by-zero and INT_MIN/-1 cases.\n+\n+  This keeps the pipeline single-cycle, preserves RV32M and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS semantics, and avoids the failed normalization/sharing approach. The expected benefit is primarily Fmax: common RV32I paths should see less divider-related switching, fanout, and routing pressure in the EX ALU result mux without changing IPC, RVFI ordering, memory behavior, or the nret=1 top-level contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Introduce gated div/rem operand wires and use them in the existing DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU case arms while leaving ALTOPS and multiply logic unchanged.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Retain or extend RV32M divide/remainder vectors for divide-by-zero, signed overflow, signed operands, and unsigned corner cases after the operand-gating refactor.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,19 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r6s0\n+title: Gate divider operands only\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best bench core already benefited strongly from isolating the MUL-family datapath from ordinary RV32I ALU operations. The remaining DIV/REM operators still consume the live ALU operands directly, so yosys may keep wide divider/remainder cones and routing coupled to the EX-stage result mux even when CoreMark is mostly executing adds, compares, loads, stores, and branches.\n+\n+  A prior attempt to share the divider datapath regressed because it introduced signed normalization, restore muxing, and simultaneous quotient/remainder logic. The safer micro-optimization is to avoid that structural rewrite and only gate the raw divider operands outside actual DIV/REM operations.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add an is_divrem_op decode inside rtl/alu.sv and feed the real a/b operands to division and remainder operators only for ALU_DIV, ALU_DIVU, ALU_REM, and ALU_REMU. For all other ALU ops, drive the divider operand wires with harmless constants, then use those gated wires in the existing RV32M divide-by-zero and INT_MIN/-1 cases.\n+\n+  This keeps the pipeline single-cycle, preserves RV32M and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS semantics, and avoids the failed normalization/sharing approach. The expected benefit is primarily Fmax: common RV32I paths should see less divider-related switching, fanout, and routing pressure in the EX ALU result mux without changing IPC, RVFI ordering, memory behavior, or the nret=1 top-level contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Introduce gated div/rem operand wires and use them in the existing DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU case arms while leaving ALTOPS and multiply logic unchanged.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Retain or extend RV32M divide/remainder vectors for divide-by-zero, signed overflow, signed operands, and unsigned corner cases after the operand-gating refactor.\"\n","additions":19,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778689265170,"end":1778689265173}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f916818324491fd016a04a4dceed48198a3c3574de0d67e07"}},"id":"prt_e2223ff63001x9oFTTxx4dj2aY","sessionID":"ses_1dddcad38ffeyUtl5MmkF32bVm","messageID":"msg_e2223f382001mkC5yW7yJ2219E"}}
