ng approach. The expected benefit is primarily Fmax: common RV32I paths should see less divider-related switching, fanout, and routing pressure in the EX ALU result mux without changing IPC, RVFI ordering, memory behavior, or the nret=1 top-level contract.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n    description: \"Introduce gated div/rem operand wires and use them in the existing DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU case arms while leaving ALTOPS and multiply logic unchanged.\"\n  - file: test/test_alu.py\n    description: \"Retain or extend RV32M divide/remainder vectors for divide-by-zero, signed overflow, signed operands, and unsigned corner cases after the operand-gating refactor.\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778689273460,"end":1778689273467}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_000b2b829be341d9016a04a4f84d94819aa494c0399c588cd9"}},"id":"prt_e22246acf001fJcK2w2GhSZl7K","sessionID":"ses_1dddcad38ffeyUtl5MmkF32bVm","messageID":"msg_e22244ed40011SiUuZxwcPdfd4"}}
