{"type":"text","timestamp":1778695052589,"sessionID":"ses_1dd83ef47ffeEBkS2jr5fRmCHg","part":{"id":"prt_e227c986e001FefLTuAa31rEUQ","messageID":"msg_e227c44cb001hA4JsdFS7ahsz0","sessionID":"ses_1dd83ef47ffeEBkS2jr5fRmCHg","type":"text","text":"Prior micro-opt attempts show arithmetic gating beyond the multiplier has mostly regressed. The safest remaining micro-opt angle is dead metadata trimming: remove pipeline fields/control bits that are currently carried through registers but never consumed, reducing FF/LUT routing without changing timing policy or architectural behavior.","time":{"start":1778695051374,"end":1778695052587},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_03a8c652e23d0ce2016a04bb8b41d0819bbb744728539a26f0","phase":"commentary"}}}}
