{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778695082138,"sessionID":"ses_1dd83ef47ffeEBkS2jr5fRmCHg","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_4VNlTko5CLB3wZT0KCH6Z70W","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r7s0\n+title: \"Trim dead pipeline metadata\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core has already benefited from narrow datapath cleanup, while later attempts to add gating, prediction, buffering, or divider rewrites mostly lost Fmax or broke formal. There are still dead bits carried through hot pipeline bundles: ctrl.is_lui is decoded but never consumed, and EX/MEM branch_taken/branch_target are written but not read by MEM, WB, RVFI, hazard, or forwarding logic. On a small FPGA these unused flops and their assignment cones can still consume routing, reset/load muxing, and placement freedom.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove unused pipeline metadata instead of adding new behavior. Delete ctrl_t.is_lui and its decoder/id_stage assignments, and delete ex_mem_t.branch_taken and ex_mem_t.branch_target plus the corresponding ex_stage register writes. LUI behavior is already represented by ALU_LUI with alu_src/reg_write, branch redirects use the combinational EX outputs, and RVFI pc_next uses the resolved value already stored in EX/MEM, so these fields should not affect architectural state or retirement.\n+\n+  This is a pure micro-optimization: fewer registered bits, less control fanout, and less unnecessary mux/load/reset logic in the ID/EX and EX/MEM registers. The expected gain is modest but safer than another arithmetic or predictor change because it does not change pipeline depth, hazard policy, bus behavior, RVFI ordering, or RV32IM semantics.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove unused ctrl_t.is_lui and unused ex_mem_t branch_taken/branch_target fields from the pipeline bundle definitions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Stop emitting the unused is_lui control bit while preserving LUI legality, ALU_LUI selection, alu_src, and reg_write behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Drop dec_is_lui wiring and ctrl_decoded.is_lui assignment so ID/EX carries one fewer dead control bit.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove writes to the dead EX/MEM branch_taken and branch_target fields while keeping redirect, redirect_target, misalignment trap, and pc_next behavior unchanged.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r7s0\n+title: \"Trim dead pipeline metadata\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core has already benefited from narrow datapath cleanup, while later attempts to add gating, prediction, buffering, or divider rewrites mostly lost Fmax or broke formal. There are still dead bits carried through hot pipeline bundles: ctrl.is_lui is decoded but never consumed, and EX/MEM branch_taken/branch_target are written but not read by MEM, WB, RVFI, hazard, or forwarding logic. On a small FPGA these unused flops and their assignment cones can still consume routing, reset/load muxing, and placement freedom.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove unused pipeline metadata instead of adding new behavior. Delete ctrl_t.is_lui and its decoder/id_stage assignments, and delete ex_mem_t.branch_taken and ex_mem_t.branch_target plus the corresponding ex_stage register writes. LUI behavior is already represented by ALU_LUI with alu_src/reg_write, branch redirects use the combinational EX outputs, and RVFI pc_next uses the resolved value already stored in EX/MEM, so these fields should not affect architectural state or retirement.\n+\n+  This is a pure micro-optimization: fewer registered bits, less control fanout, and less unnecessary mux/load/reset logic in the ID/EX and EX/MEM registers. The expected gain is modest but safer than another arithmetic or predictor change because it does not change pipeline depth, hazard policy, bus behavior, RVFI ordering, or RV32IM semantics.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove unused ctrl_t.is_lui and unused ex_mem_t branch_taken/branch_target fields from the pipeline bundle definitions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Stop emitting the unused is_lui control bit while preserving LUI legality, ALU_LUI selection, alu_src, and reg_write behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Drop dec_is_lui wiring and ctrl_decoded.is_lui assignment so ID/EX carries one fewer dead control bit.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove writes to the dead EX/MEM branch_taken and branch_target fields while keeping redirect, redirect_target, misalignment trap, and pc_next behavior unchanged.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonett