{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1778699143034,"sessionID":"ses_1dd453af2ffeamtNE121QySfCg","part":{"id":"prt_e22bb0779001LAUmqXgSgFJipJ","messageID":"msg_e22baf8b40013yx0GZEB7NySlR","sessionID":"ses_1dd453af2ffeamtNE121QySfCg","snapshot":"3f85c90f7917ca1075c824415218518763cd4125","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778699165035,"sessionID":"ses_1dd453af2ffeamtNE121QySfCg","part":{"id":"prt_e22bb5896002wkSN9bzVdOkd1Y","messageID":"msg_e22baf8b40013yx0GZEB7NySlR","sessionID":"ses_1dd453af2ffeamtNE121QySfCg","type":"text","text":"The structural history is mostly negative except the decode-side PC target retiming already present in the current RTL. I’m going to propose a narrow structural split that preserves cycle timing: move RV32M arithmetic into a separate combinational side module and keep the main ALU as an RV32I/address/control fast path, aiming to improve synthesis isolation without adding stalls.","time":{"start":1778699163798,"end":1778699165035},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0dff63b724445d3a016a04cb9bb1c8819ab53e7f89da83b749","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778699188250,"sessionID":"ses_1dd453af2ffeamtNE121QySfCg","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_ESTA3CbCJbhsKphipWme8lTC","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r11s1\n+title: \"Split M arithmetic sidecar\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The successful current best isolated the MUL-family datapath inside the ALU, but the EX-stage result mux still mixes ordinary RV32I operations, memory address generation, branch support, multiply, and divide/remainder in one large combinational block. Prior structural attempts that added stalls, predictors, fetch buffers, or broad pipeline retiming mostly regressed, so the next structural angle should preserve the existing five-stage timing and IPC while giving synthesis a cleaner separation between the hot RV32I path and rarely used M-extension hardware.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split the current monolithic ALU into a small RV32I fast ALU plus a separate combinational RV32M sidecar module. The fast ALU handles ADD/SUB/logical/compare/shift/LUI and remains the default source for CoreMark's common arithmetic, branch compare operands, and load/store address generation. The M sidecar receives gated operands only for MUL/DIV/REM opcodes and returns an M result that is selected at the final EX result mux when the decoded op is an M instruction.\n+\n+  This is intentionally not a multicycle M-unit: it preserves single-cycle retirement behavior, forwarding, load-use handling, RVFI metadata, and the nret=1 interface. The expected benefit is mostly Fmax and routing quality from reducing fanout and logic sharing pressure in the RV32I ALU cone while keeping the already-good shared multiplier semantics and exact RV32M division corner cases unchanged.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Refactor the existing ALU into an RV32I fast path and a final M-result select, preserving RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS and exact RV32M corner-case behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/m_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a combinational RV32M sidecar containing the shared multiplier and existing DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU semantics with operands gated outside M opcodes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate or wire the split ALU structure without changing EX/MEM timing, redirect behavior, forwarding inputs, or RVFI-visible results.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Retain and extend ALU vectors around MULH/MULHU/MULHSU and DIV/REM edge cases to guard the structural split.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r11s1\n+title: \"Split M arithmetic sidecar\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The successful current best isolated the MUL-family datapath inside the ALU, but the EX-stage result mux still mixes ordinary RV32I operations, memory address generation, branch support, multiply, and divide/remainder in one large combinational block. Prior structural attempts that added stalls, predictors, fetch buffers, or broad pipeline retiming mostly regressed, so the next structural angle should preserve the existing five-stage timing and IPC while giving synthesis a cleaner separation between the hot RV32I path and rarely used M-extension hardware.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split the current monolithic ALU into a small RV32I fast ALU plus a separate combinational RV32M sidecar module. The fast ALU handles ADD/SUB/logical/compare/shift/LUI and remains the default source for CoreMark's common arithmetic, branch compare operands, and load/store address generation. The M sidecar receives gated operands only for MUL/DIV/REM opcodes and returns an M result that is selected at the final EX result mux when the decoded op is an M instruction.\n+\n+  This is intentionally not a multicycle M-unit: it preserves single-cycle retirement behavior, forwarding, load-use handling, RVFI metadata, and the nret=1 interface. The expected benefit is mostly Fmax and routing quality from reducing fanout and logic sharing pressure in the RV32I ALU cone while keeping the already-good shared multiplier semantics and exact RV32M division corner cases unchanged.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Refactor the existing ALU into an RV32I fast path and a final M-result select, preserving RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS and exact RV32M corner-case behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/m_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a combinational RV32M sidecar containing the shared multiplier and existing DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU semantics with operands gated outside M opcodes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate or wire the split ALU structure without changing EX/MEM timing, redirect behavior, forwarding inputs, or RVFI-visible results.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Retain and extend ALU vectors around MULH/MULHU/MULHSU and DIV/REM edge cases to guard the structural split.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/