{"type":"text","timestamp":1778700117356,"sessionID":"ses_1dd36d9e6ffeaJizEec0sNgQyI","part":{"id":"prt_e22c9e317001u7CLJF1GcjTV1C","messageID":"msg_e22c94cb5001OR4HP12oRWoNMx","sessionID":"ses_1dd36d9e6ffeaJizEec0sNgQyI","type":"text","text":"Structural history shows most IPC-overlap/prediction retiming ideas regressed, while the only still-plausible structural gap is the broken divider split: the lesson was handshake correctness, not measured performance failure. I’m writing a focused hypothesis for a clean divider-only EX hold protocol that preserves the successful single-cycle multiply path.","time":{"start":1778700116759,"end":1778700117355},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0eb3719c0c481294016a04cf549ffc8199b4b5ec3d03b97b99","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778700142535,"sessionID":"ses_1dd36d9e6ffeaJizEec0sNgQyI","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_yqjBoOedfd8dbYpcZFvEKgC0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r12s1\n+title: Clean divider EX handshake\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core still carries full combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU\n+  operators in the ALU result cone, while the successful multiply sharing pass\n+  already removed much of the always-live M-extension pressure. Prior broad\n+  multicycle M-unit attempts regressed or broke because they stalled common\n+  multiply operations and used ad hoc control that desynchronized EX/MEM and\n+  RVFI payloads. A divider-only structural split remains attractive if the EX\n+  stage owns a precise valid/hold/done handshake and captures the entire\n+  instruction payload atomically with the divider result.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace only the real DIV/REM combinational datapath with an iterative or\n+  staged divider unit that starts when a valid divider-class instruction enters\n+  EX. While the divider is busy, hold PC, ID/EX, and the in-flight EX payload;\n+  do not bubble EX/MEM with partial metadata. When done, commit exactly one\n+  EX/MEM register update containing the original instruction metadata,\n+  forwarded rs values, pc_next, control bits, and the final quotient or\n+  remainder. Keep RV32I and the existing shared multiply family single-cycle.\n+\n+  This should improve Fmax by removing the remaining same-cycle divide and\n+  remainder cones from the hot ALU path, with limited CoreMark IPC cost because\n+  divider-class instructions are much rarer than ordinary ALU, branch, memory,\n+  and multiply operations. The key structural change versus the broken prior\n+  divider attempt is a single owner for divider state inside EX and an atomic\n+  EX/MEM capture on completion, preserving RVFI order and payload alignment.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU operators from the normal combinational ALU path while preserving RV32I, shared multiply, and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a divider-only busy/done state machine that holds the original EX payload and updates EX/MEM atomically when the result is ready.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an EX divider busy stall input that freezes fetch/decode consistently without flushing or duplicating retirements.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the divider busy stall between EX and the hazard/control path without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"If needed, add a compact divider operation/result encoding while keeping pipeline bundle metadata aligned with RVFI.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,41 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r12s1\n+title: Clean divider EX handshake\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core still carries full combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU\n+  operators in the ALU result cone, while the successful multiply sharing pass\n+  already removed much of the always-live M-extension pressure. Prior broad\n+  multicycle M-unit attempts regressed or broke because they stalled common\n+  multiply operations and used ad hoc control that desynchronized EX/MEM and\n+  RVFI payloads. A divider-only structural split remains attractive if the EX\n+  stage owns a precise valid/hold/done handshake and captures the entire\n+  instruction payload atomically with the divider result.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace only the real DIV/REM combinational datapath with an iterative or\n+  staged divider unit that starts when a valid divider-class instruction enters\n+  EX. While the divider is busy, hold PC, ID/EX, and the in-flight EX payload;\n+  do not bubble EX/MEM with partial metadata. When done, commit exactly one\n+  EX/MEM register update containing the original instruction metadata,\n+  forwarded rs values, pc_next, control bits, and the final quotient or\n+  remainder. Keep RV32I and the existing shared multiply family single-cycle.\n+\n+  This should improve Fmax by removing the remaining same-cycle divide and\n+  remainder cones from the hot ALU path, with limited CoreMark IPC cost because\n+  divider-class instructions are much rarer than ordinary ALU, branch, memory,\n+  and multiply operations. The key structural change versus the broken prior\n+  divider attempt is a single owner for divider state inside EX and an atomic\n+  EX/MEM capture on completion, preserving RVFI order and payload alignment.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU operators from the normal combinational ALU path while preserving RV32I, shared multiply, and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a divider-only busy/done state machine that holds the original EX payload and updates EX/MEM atomically when the result is ready.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an EX divider busy stall input that freezes fetch/decode consistently without flushing or duplicating retirements.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the divider busy stall between EX and the hazard/control path without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"If needed, add a compact divider operation/result encoding while keeping pipeline bundle metadata aligned with RVFI.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,41 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r12s1\n+title: Clean divider EX handshake\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core still carries full combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU\n+  operators in the ALU result cone, while the successful multiply sharing pass\n+  already removed much of the always-live M-extension pressure. Prior broad\n+  multicycle M-unit attempts regressed or broke because they stalled common\n+  multiply operations and used ad hoc control that desynchronized EX/MEM and\n+  RVFI payloads. A divider-only structural split remains attractive if the EX\n+  stage owns a precise valid/hold/done handshake and captures the entire\n+  instruction payload atomically with the divider result.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace only the real DIV/REM combinational datapath with an iterative or\n+  staged divider unit that starts when a valid divider-class instruction enters\n+  EX. While the divider is busy, hold PC, ID/EX, and the in-flight EX payload;\n+  do not bubble EX/MEM with partial metadata. When done, commit exactly one\n+  EX/MEM register update containing the original instruction metadata,\n+  forwarded rs values, pc_next, control bits, and the final quotient or\n+  remainder. Keep RV32I and the existing shared multiply family single-cycle.\n+\n+  This should improve Fmax by removing the remaining same-cycle divide and\n+  remainder cones from the hot ALU path, with limited CoreMark IPC cost because\n+  divider-class instructions are much rarer than ordinary ALU, branch, memory,\n+  and multiply operations. The key structural change versus the broken prior\n+  divider attempt is a single owner for divider state inside EX and an atomic\n+  EX/MEM capture on completion, preserving RVFI order and payload alignment.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU operators from the normal combinational ALU path while preserving RV32I, shared multiply, and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a divider-only busy/done state machine that holds the original EX payload and updates EX/MEM atomically when the result is ready.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an EX divider busy stall input that freezes fetch/decode consistently without flushing or duplicating retirements.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the divider busy stall between EX and the hazard/control path without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"If needed, add a compact divider operation/result encoding while keeping pipeline bundle metadata aligned with RVFI.\"\n","a