23:   remainder cones from the hot ALU path, with limited CoreMark IPC cost because\n24:   divider-class instructions are much rarer than ordinary ALU, branch, memory,\n25:   and multiply operations. The key structural change versus the broken prior\n26:   divider attempt is a single owner for divider state inside EX and an atomic\n27:   EX/MEM capture on completion, preserving RVFI order and payload alignment.\n28: expected_impact:\n29:   fitness_delta_pct: 5\n30:   confidence: medium\n31: changes:\n32:   - file: rtl/alu.sv\n33:     description: \"Remove real DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU operators from the normal combinational ALU path while preserving RV32I, shared multiply, and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS behavior.\"\n34:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n35:     description: \"Add a divider-only busy/done state machine that holds the original EX payload and updates EX/MEM atomically when the result is ready.\"\n36:   - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n37:     description: \"Add an EX divider busy stall input that freezes fetch/decode consistently without flushing or duplicating retirements.\"\n38:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n39:     description: \"Wire the divider busy stall between EX and the hazard/control path without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n40:   - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n41:     description: \"If needed, add a compact divider operation/result encoding while keeping pipeline bundle metadata aligned with RVFI.\"\n\n(End of file - total 41 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260513-002-r12s1\ntitle: Clean divider EX handshake\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  The current best core still carries full combinational DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU\n  operators in the ALU result cone, while the successful multiply sharing pass\n  already removed much of the always-live M-extension pressure. Prior broad\n  multicycle M-unit attempts regressed or broke because they stalled common\n  multiply operations and used ad hoc control that desynchronized EX/MEM and\n  RVFI payloads. A divider-only structural split remains attractive if the EX\n  stage owns a precise valid/hold/done handshake and captures the entire\n  instruction payload atomically with the divider result.\nhypothesis: |\n  Replace only the real DIV/REM combinational datapath with an iterative or\n  staged divider unit that starts when a valid divider-class instruction enters\n  EX. While the divider is busy, hold PC, ID/EX, and the in-flight EX payload;\n  do not bubble EX/MEM with partial metadata. When done, commit exactly one\n  EX/MEM register update containing the original instruction metadata,\n  forwarded rs values, pc_next, control bits, and the final quotient or\n  remainder. Keep RV32I and the existing shared multiply family single-cycle.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778700148337,"end":1778700148341}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0585f00d2ab57982016a04cf71ec1c819990db87e54a292f98"}},"id":"prt_e22ca5563001AjhUE4r4Eh2uki","sessionID":"ses_1dd36d9e6ffeaJizEec0sNgQyI","messageID":"msg_e22ca482f001iaa8dgql4Hlcdk"}}
