{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1778700903314,"sessionID":"ses_1dd2a561effeaTIjFEKGAY0mBG","part":{"id":"prt_e22d5e391001OIRAqbUaqVpTgM","messageID":"msg_e22d5df10001PtivXiQIcKgUhK","sessionID":"ses_1dd2a561effeaTIjFEKGAY0mBG","snapshot":"7bdbfdb757d998eb30067537f8baf78f17a27b0c","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778700927353,"sessionID":"ses_1dd2a561effeaTIjFEKGAY0mBG","part":{"id":"prt_e22d63b13002tVlBPBO8FdMlQQ","messageID":"msg_e22d5df10001PtivXiQIcKgUhK","sessionID":"ses_1dd2a561effeaTIjFEKGAY0mBG","type":"text","text":"The structural history is mostly negative; the only successful structural change was pure retiming that shortened EX without changing IPC. I’m going to propose a similarly conservative structural retime: carry a predecoded “uses both sources/uses rs2” control bit through decode for forwarding/hazard only, but avoid changing RVFI operand metadata or adding front-end prediction/state.","time":{"start":1778700925715,"end":1778700927353},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_016c8b161d538994016a04d27d9bc08198876d25627df9853b","phase":"commentary"}}}}
