{"type":"text","timestamp":1778700941701,"sessionID":"ses_1dd2a561effeaTIjFEKGAY0mBG","part":{"id":"prt_e22d6730f001E0cDpP9SgSfj8b","messageID":"msg_e22d66bbd002Es4tVggrchg4mu","sessionID":"ses_1dd2a561effeaTIjFEKGAY0mBG","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis file now. The proposal is intentionally narrow because prior structural changes that added state, prediction, or new bypass paths consistently lost timing.","time":{"start":1778700940048,"end":1778700941700},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0da52b73126a8d7f016a04d28bf1dc8198b6f6bb54d66129f7","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778700965720,"sessionID":"ses_1dd2a561effeaTIjFEKGAY0mBG","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_k3iqp6UCTTICLnMAGFsVlRGA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r13s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r13s1\n+title: \"Hazard-local source-use bits\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current load-use interlock compares a load destination against both raw source fields of the following instruction, even when the following instruction does not architecturally consume one of those fields. CoreMark has enough pointer and immediate-heavy code that false load-use bubbles can reduce iterations per cycle, especially under the random stall model.\n+\n+  Two earlier source-qualification attempts broke because they either used approximate opcode logic or let source-use information alter RVFI/register metadata. The lesson is useful: source-use qualification should exist only in the hazard decision, while rs addresses, rs data, forwarding payloads, and retirement metadata remain exactly as they are today.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add exact decoder-derived uses_rs1 and uses_rs2 signals for the current IF/ID instruction and feed them only into hazard_unit. The load-use detector should stall only when the pending load's rd matches a source field that the younger instruction truly reads; it must not zero or mask ID/EX source fields, regfile read addresses, forwarding metadata, or RVFI rs fields.\n+\n+  This is a structural control-path cleanup rather than a predictor or datapath rewrite. It preserves the five-stage pipeline, nret=1 RVFI contract, memory behavior, forwarding paths, and all retirement metadata, while removing unnecessary bubbles after loads followed by OP-IMM, LOAD, LUI, AUIPC, JAL, FENCE, EBREAK, or other one/no-source instructions. The expected upside is IPC rather than Fmax, with lower timing risk than store buffers, fetch buffers, same-cycle load bypassing, or branch prediction.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Expose exact uses_rs1 and uses_rs2 outputs alongside existing control signals, clearing them only for instruction forms that do not architecturally read the corresponding source field.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the decoder's source-use outputs through combinational decode for the current IF/ID instruction without changing the ID/EX payload or RVFI-visible source metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Connect the hazard-local source-use signals from ID/decode to hazard_unit while leaving regfile read addresses, forwarding operands, and RVFI fields unchanged.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Gate load-use rd comparisons with uses_rs1 and uses_rs2 so only true consumers of a pending load insert the one-cycle bubble.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r13s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r13s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r13s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r13s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,23 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r13s1\n+title: \"Hazard-local source-use bits\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current load-use interlock compares a load destination against both raw source fields of the following instruction, even wh