{"type":"text","timestamp":1778701919740,"sessionID":"ses_1dd1aeb89ffeJCqEFe5oYe2h1H","part":{"id":"prt_e22e55b390017IsiFbkSFKQD5s","messageID":"msg_e22e53ffd0013cR92S2zsxyWBo","sessionID":"ses_1dd1aeb89ffeJCqEFe5oYe2h1H","type":"text","text":"Prior structural results show that added front-end state, prediction, store buffering, load bypasses, and divider handshakes have mostly regressed or broken. The least-overlapped remaining structural angle is a small retiming of branch-condition generation into ID/EX metadata, keeping EX as the resolution point and avoiding any new fetch redirect path.","time":{"start":1778701916985,"end":1778701919737},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_07a3d57a78c631ff016a04d65ce0f0819bbae0e91cde3f42c7","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778701940144,"sessionID":"ses_1dd1aeb89ffeJCqEFe5oYe2h1H","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_6A5VirncV44rGwZkFHDjjUJw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r14s1\n+title: \"Predecode branch compare class\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage still decodes the branch comparison class from branch_op\n+  while it is also resolving forwarded operands, ALU output, redirect, and RVFI\n+  pc_next. Prior front-end prediction and target-injection attempts regressed\n+  because they added fetch-PC muxing or mutable prediction metadata, while the\n+  successful structural win was a pure ID-to-EX retiming of PC target values.\n+\n+  A similarly narrow retiming can move branch comparator control preparation out\n+  of the EX hot path without changing when branches resolve, adding pipeline\n+  latency, or touching memory/M-extension behavior.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add compact decoded branch-compare control bits to the ID/EX pipeline payload,\n+  derived from the already-decoded branch_op in ID. EX should use those registered\n+  bits to select equality, signed-less-than, or unsigned-less-than comparison and\n+  a final invert flag, instead of carrying the raw funct3-style branch_op through\n+  a full case statement on the EX redirect path.\n+\n+  This preserves the five-stage pipeline, single nret=1 retirement contract,\n+  existing forwarding operands, misalignment trap behavior, and EX-stage branch\n+  resolution point. The expected gain is Fmax from simplifying the branch\n+  condition/control cone in EX; IPC should be unchanged because no prediction,\n+  stalls, or retire semantics are modified.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Extend the ID/EX payload with registered compact branch compare control bits while preserving existing RVFI-visible fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Derive branch equality/less-than selection and invert metadata from decoded branch_op and latch it into ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the EX branch_op case with the registered compare metadata, keeping redirect, pc_next, and misalignment trap behavior unchanged.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r14s1\n+title: \"Predecode branch compare class\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage still decodes the branch comparison class from branch_op\n+  while it is also resolving forwarded operands, ALU output, redirect, and RVFI\n+  pc_next. Prior front-end prediction and target-injection attempts regressed\n+  because they added fetch-PC muxing or mutable prediction metadata, while the\n+  successful structural win was a pure ID-to-EX retiming of PC target values.\n+\n+  A similarly narrow retiming can move branch comparator control preparation out\n+  of the EX hot path without changing when branches resolve, adding pipeline\n+  latency, or touching memory/M-extension behavior.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add compact decoded branch-compare control bits to the ID/EX pipeline payload,\n+  derived from the already-decoded branch_op in ID. EX should use those registered\n+  bits to select equality, signed-less-than, or unsigned-less-than comparison and\n+  a final invert flag, instead of carrying the raw funct3-style branch_op through\n+  a full case statement on the EX redirect path.\n+\n+  This preserves the five-stage pipeline, single nret=1 retirement contract,\n+  existing forwarding operands, misalignment trap behavior, and EX-stage branch\n+  resolution point. The expected gain is Fmax from simplifying the branch\n+  condition/control cone in EX; IPC should be unchanged because no prediction,\n+  stalls, or retire semantics are modified.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Extend the ID/EX payload with registered compact branch compare control bits while preserving existing RVFI-visible fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Derive branch equality/less-than selection and invert metadata from decoded branch_op and latch it into ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the EX branch_op case with the registered compare metadata, keeping redirect, pc_next, and misalignment trap behavior unchanged.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r14s1\n+title: \"Predecode branch compare class\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage still decodes the branch comparison class from branch_op\n+  while it is also resolving forwarded operands, ALU output, redirect, and RVFI\n+  pc_next. Prior front-end prediction and target-injection attempts regressed\n+  because they added fetch-PC muxing or mutable prediction metadata, while the\n+  successful structural win was a pure ID-to-EX retiming of PC target values.\n+\n+  A similarly narrow retiming can move branch comparator control preparation out\n+  of the EX hot path without changing when branches resolve, adding pipeline\n+  latency, or touching memory/M-extension behavior.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add compact decoded branch-compare control bits to the ID/EX pipeline payload,\n+  derived from the already-decoded branch_op in ID. EX should use those registered\n+  bits to select equality, signed-less-than, or unsigned-less-than comparison and\n+  a final invert flag, instead of carrying the raw funct3-style branch_op through\n+  a full case statement on the EX redirect path.\n+\n+  This preserves the five-stage pipeline, single nret=1 retirement contract,\n+  existing forwarding operands, misalignment trap behavior, and EX-stage branch\n+  resolution point. The expected gain is Fmax from simplifying the branch\n+  condition/control cone in EX; IPC should be unchanged because no prediction,\n+  stalls, or retire semantics are modified.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Extend the ID/EX payload with registered compact branch compare control bits while preserving existing RVFI-visible fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Derive branch equality/less-than selection and invert metadata from decoded branch_op and latch it into ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the EX branch_op case with the registered compare metadata, keeping redirect, pc_next, and misalignment trap behavior unchanged.\"\n","additions":35,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778701940136,"end":1778701940142}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07a3d57a78c631ff016a04d65f8974819b86f7b5b2c2924114"}},"id":"prt_e22e565fd001qNnHIWJz0E5RQa","sessionID":"ses_1dd1aeb89ffeJCqEFe5oYe2h1H","messageID":"msg_e22e53ffd0013cR92S2zsxyWBo"}}
