{"type":"text","timestamp":1778703094521,"sessionID":"ses_1dd09827bffegaQ5TLDV4QLeqp","part":{"id":"prt_e22f74b38001FoaxXbl1MZrZeI","messageID":"msg_e22f7412a002doRqebyKl2T8Ki","sessionID":"ses_1dd09827bffegaQ5TLDV4QLeqp","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a narrow structural hypothesis that retimes RVFI `pc_next` construction out of the EX-stage register input cone, preserving branch resolution and IPC while avoiding the failed predictor/front-end patterns.","time":{"start":1778703092536,"end":1778703094519},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_06ff1b3234d09759016a04daf471d08198b682a99b6ab2f563","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778703113669,"sessionID":"ses_1dd09827bffegaQ5TLDV4QLeqp","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_hLjA78S3qRVmDWgNsF2UsgqJ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r15s1\n+title: \"Retire PC-next in MEM\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The only structural improvement that has held up so far was a pure retiming of PC-relative sums from EX back into ID. Most later structural attempts regressed by adding front-end PC muxes, same-cycle load-data paths, store-buffer control, or wider prediction metadata. The current EX stage still builds the RVFI next-PC value in the same block that resolves redirects, selects jump link data, runs forwarding, and captures EX/MEM, even though the RVFI pc_wdata value is not observed until retirement.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Move RVFI pc_next construction from EX into the MEM/WB capture path. EX should continue resolving branch/jump redirects exactly as today, but EX/MEM only needs to carry the resolved control-flow target and branch-taken state; mem_stage can compute the retiring pc_next from registered EX/MEM metadata as either pc+4 or the resolved target before writing MEM/WB.\n+\n+  This keeps the five-stage pipeline, nret=1 RVFI contract, load-use behavior, redirect timing, and CoreMark IPC unchanged. The expected benefit is Fmax from shortening the EX-stage register input cone and reducing fanout around the pc_next mux, while avoiding any new fetch-side feedback or predictor state that prior structural attempts showed to be expensive on Tang Nano 20K.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Adjust EX/MEM metadata so it carries a resolved control-flow target instead of a fully selected pc_next value; keep MEM/WB pc_next for RVFI retirement.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Stop building the final RVFI pc_next mux on the EX register input; preserve redirect, misalignment trap handling, jump link data, and branch target metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute and register MEM/WB pc_next from EX/MEM pc, resolved target, branch-taken, jump, and trap metadata immediately before retirement.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,19 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r15s1\n+title: \"Retire PC-next in MEM\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The only structural improvement that has held up so far was a pure retiming of PC-relative sums from EX back into ID. Most later structural attempts regressed by adding front-end PC muxes, same-cycle load-data paths, store-buffer control, or wider prediction metadata. The current EX stage still builds the RVFI next-PC value in the same block that resolves redirects, selects jump link data, runs forwarding, and captures EX/MEM, even though the RVFI pc_wdata value is not observed until retirement.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Move RVFI pc_next construction from EX into the MEM/WB capture path. EX should continue resolving branch/jump redirects exactly as today, but EX/MEM only needs to carry the resolved control-flow target and branch-taken state; mem_stage can compute the retiring pc_next from registered EX/MEM metadata as either pc+4 or the resolved target before writing MEM/WB.\n+\n+  This keeps the five-stage pipeline, nret=1 RVFI contract, load-use behavior, redirect timing, and CoreMark IPC unchanged. The expected benefit is Fmax from shortening the EX-stage register input cone and reducing fanout around the pc_next mux, while avoiding any new fetch-side feedback or predictor state that prior structural attempts showed to be expensive on Tang Nano 20K.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Adjust EX/MEM metadata so it carries a resolved control-flow target instead of a fully selected pc_next value; keep MEM/WB pc_next for RVFI retirement.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Stop building the final RVFI pc_next mux on the EX register input; preserve redirect, misalignment trap handling, jump link data, and branch target metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute and register MEM/WB pc_next from EX/MEM pc, resolved target, branch-taken, jump, and trap metadata immediately before retirement.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,19 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r15s1\n+title: \"Retire PC-next in 