{"type":"text","timestamp":1778678090450,"sessionID":"ses_1de86d5efffe9fvGb8PBzEGLyd","part":{"id":"prt_e2179c750001YpNO5Uzs4sOCgi","messageID":"msg_e21798d3e001tkGrPyYDlMHgpv","sessionID":"ses_1de86d5efffe9fvGb8PBzEGLyd","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a structural hypothesis focused on pulling RV32M multiply/divide out of the single-cycle EX critical path into a multi-cycle M unit, trading rare M-op stalls for higher FPGA Fmax and lower LUT pressure.","time":{"start":1778678089552,"end":1778678090449},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0797a9c42e003857016a0479496fc8819a81ed146a19339444","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778678116298,"sessionID":"ses_1de86d5efffe9fvGb8PBzEGLyd","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_beCGBBdN0Ujlks3XkYNJawH3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r1s1\n+title: \"Move RV32M to multicycle side unit\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage contains full combinational RV32M multiply and divide logic inside the same ALU case as single-cycle integer operations. On the Tang Nano 20K this likely contributes a long critical path and high LUT pressure even though CoreMark's hot loop is dominated by simple integer, branch, and memory operations. Removing the divider and wide multiplier from the regular EX datapath should improve Fmax and may also improve placement by reducing EX fan-in.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Restructure the pipeline so RV32M operations dispatch from EX into a dedicated multicycle M unit while ordinary RV32I ALU, branch, jump, and address-generation operations remain single-cycle. When an M instruction reaches EX, hold IF/ID/EX behind it until the unit returns the result, then capture that result into EX/MEM and retire normally through the existing MEM/WB and RVFI path. This should preserve single-retire ordering and correctness while replacing the worst combinational arithmetic path with shorter iterative or staged logic; the added stalls should be infrequent enough in CoreMark to be outweighed by Fmax gains.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real multiply/divide/remainder operators from the normal combinational ALU path, keeping only simple RV32I operations and the existing RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS behavior where required.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact control metadata needed to identify M-extension operations and carry a multicycle EX result without changing the top-level nret=1 RVFI contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate and control a multicycle M unit, stall while it is busy, and mux its completed result into the existing EX/MEM register for RVFI-consistent retirement.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an EX-stage multicycle-busy stall input that freezes upstream pipeline state without double-retiring or losing dmem-stall precedence.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the M-unit busy/done stall path between EX and the hazard unit while preserving the current single-channel RVFI port set.\"\n+  - file: rtl/m_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a dedicated multicycle RV32M execution unit implementing exact RV32M multiply, divide, and remainder semantics with handshake signals for EX.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Extend or adjust cocotb coverage so RV32M results are checked through the new multicycle unit path rather than only the old combinational ALU path.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,25 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r1s1\n+title: \"Move RV32M to multicycle side unit\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage contains full combinational RV32M multiply and divide logic inside the same ALU case as single-cycle integer operations. On the Tang Nano 20K this likely contributes a long critical path and high LUT pressure even though CoreMark's hot loop is dominated by simple integer, branch, and memory operations. Removing the divider and wide multiplier from the regular EX datapath should improve Fmax and may also improve placement by reducing EX fan-in.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Restructure the pipeline so RV32M operations dispatch from EX into a dedicated multicycle M unit while ordinary RV32I ALU, branch, jump, and address-generation operations remain single-cycle. When an M instruction reaches EX, hold IF/ID/EX behind it until the unit returns the result, then capture that result into EX/MEM and retire normally through the existing MEM/WB and RVFI path. This should preserve single-retire ordering and correctness while replacing the worst combinational arithmetic path with shorter iterative or staged logic; the added stalls should be infrequent enough in CoreMark to be outweighed by Fmax gains.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real multiply/divide/remainder operators from the normal combinational ALU path, keeping only simple RV32I operations and the existing RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS behavior where required.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact control metadata needed to identify M-extension operations and carry a multicycle EX result without changing the top-level nret=1 RVFI contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate and control a multicycle M unit, stall while it is busy, and mux its completed result into the existing EX/MEM register for RVFI-consistent retirement.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an EX-stage multicycle-busy stall input that freezes upstream pipeline state without double-retiring or losing dmem-stall precedence.\"\n+  - file: