ine so RV32M operations dispatch from EX into a dedicated multicycle M unit while ordinary RV32I ALU, branch, jump, and address-generation operations remain single-cycle. When an M instruction reaches EX, hold IF/ID/EX behind it until the unit returns the result, then capture that result into EX/MEM and retire normally through the existing MEM/WB and RVFI path. This should preserve single-retire ordering and correctness while replacing the worst combinational arithmetic path with shorter iterative or staged logic; the added stalls should be infrequent enough in CoreMark to be outweighed by Fmax gains.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real multiply/divide/remainder operators from the normal combinational ALU path, keeping only simple RV32I operations and the existing RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS behavior where required.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact control metadata needed to identify M-extension operations and carry a multicycle EX result without changing the top-level nret=1 RVFI contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate and control a multicycle M unit, stall while it is busy, and mux its completed result into the existing EX/MEM register for RVFI-consistent retirement.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an EX-stage multicycle-busy stall input that freezes upstream pipeline state without double-retiring or losing dmem-stall precedence.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the M-unit busy/done stall path between EX and the hazard unit while preserving the current single-channel RVFI port set.\"\n+  - file: rtl/m_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a dedicated multicycle RV32M execution unit implementing exact RV32M multiply, divide, and remainder semantics with handshake signals for EX.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Extend or adjust cocotb coverage so RV32M resu