{"type":"text","timestamp":1778680261860,"sessionID":"ses_1de65a1e8ffeY8ylHcr6qJt41C","part":{"id":"prt_e219ae444002eZOGpF8R4cPwGg","messageID":"msg_e219a8ce50010dqzocZj5K2g4b","sessionID":"ses_1de65a1e8ffeY8ylHcr6qJt41C","type":"text","text":"The prior structural attempts were the M side unit and ready-load bypass; both lost fitness because they added stalls or lengthened the load-data critical path. I’m choosing a different structural hypothesis: add a real IF/ID fetch register/skid point to cut the current imem-to-decode-to-ID/EX path, targeting Fmax without touching RV32M or load-use timing.","time":{"start":1778680259652,"end":1778680261860},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_086dcde33d3b4803016a0481c38b4c819ab131fccaf9014843","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778680281027,"sessionID":"ses_1de65a1e8ffeY8ylHcr6qJt41C","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_OLMshdjvEpf1XTCN9BUrqso7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r3s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r3s1\n+title: \"Register fetch-decode boundary\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core has no real IF/ID pipeline register: the fetched instruction and PC flow combinationally from the PC/imem side into decoder, immediate generation, regfile read addressing, hazard detection, and the ID/EX register. That likely creates a broad timing path through external instruction data and decode fanout, and prior predictor work showed that adding more fetch/decode combinational logic can severely hurt Fmax.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Convert the IF/ID boundary into a registered fetch-decode stage, optionally with a one-entry valid/skid behavior for stalls, so imem_data and pc are captured before decode. Preserve the existing single-retire RVFI contract and branch/load-use/dmem stall semantics by flushing or holding the registered IF/ID payload using the same hazard priorities. This should shorten the highest-fanout front-end timing path and improve FPGA Fmax with only a small control change and no new load-data or RV32M critical path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Keep or minimally adjust the IF/ID bundle so it can represent a registered valid payload and bubble without changing RVFI-visible pipeline metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add an IF/ID register or one-entry fetch buffer that captures pc, instruction, and valid, with redirect and flush taking priority over holds.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Review stall and flush priorities for the registered fetch-decode boundary so load-use, imem stall, dmem stall, and redirect behavior remain precise.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the revised IF/ID registered stage into the existing decode, hazard, and RVFI-preserving pipeline without changing the top-level nret=1 IO contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r3s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r3s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r3s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r3s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,19 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r3s1\n+title: \"Register fetch-decode boundary\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core has no real IF/ID pipeline register: the fetched instruction and PC flow combinationally from the PC/imem side into decoder, immediate generation, regfile read addressing, hazard detection, and the ID/EX register. That likely creates a broad timing path through external instruction data and decode fanout, and prior predictor work showed that adding more fetch/decode combinational logic can severely hurt Fmax.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Convert the IF/ID boundary into a registered fetch-decode stage, optionally with a one-entry valid/skid behavior for stalls, so imem_data and pc are captured before decode. Preserve the existing single-retire RVFI contract and branch/load-use/dmem stall semantics by flushing or holding the registered IF/ID payload using the same hazard priorities. This should shorten the highest-fanout front-end timing path and improve FPGA Fmax with only a small control change and no new load-data or RV32M critical path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Keep or minimally adjust the IF/ID bundle so it can represent a registered valid payload and bubble without changing RVFI-visible pipeline metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add an IF/ID register or one-entry fetch buffer that captures pc, instruction, and valid, with redirect and flush taking priority over holds.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Review stall and flush priorities for the registered fetch-decode boundary so load-use, imem stall, dmem stall, and redirect behavior remain precise.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the revised IF/ID registered stage into the existing decode, hazard, and RVFI-preserving pipeline without changing the top-level nret=1 IO contract.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r3s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r3s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r3s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r3s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r3s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,19 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r3s1\n+title: \"Register fetch-decode boundary\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core has no real IF/ID pipeline register: the fetched instruction and PC flow combinationally from the PC/imem side into decoder, immediate generation, regfile read addressing, hazard detection, and the ID/EX register. That likely creates a broad timing path through external instruction data and decode fanout, and prior predictor work showed that adding more fetch/decode combinational logic can severely hurt Fmax.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Convert the IF/ID boundary into a registered fetch-decode stage, optionally with a one-entry valid/skid behavior for stalls, so imem_data and pc are captured before decode. Preserve the existing single-retire RVFI contract and branch/load-use/dmem stall semantics by flushing or holding the registered IF/ID payload using the same hazard priorities. This should shorten the highest-fanout front-end timing path and improve FPGA Fmax with only a small control change and no new load-data or RV32M critical path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Keep or minimally adjust the IF/ID bundle so it can represent a registered valid payload and bubble without changing RVFI-visible pipeline metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add an IF/ID register or one-entry fetch buffer that captures pc, instruction, and valid, with redirect and flush taking priority over holds.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Review stall and flush priorities for the registered fetch-decode boundary so load-use, imem stall, dmem stall, and redirect behavior remain precise.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the revised IF/ID registered stage into the existing decode, hazard, and RVFI-preserving pipeline without changing the top-level nret=1 IO contract.\"\n","additions":19,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r3s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778680281024,"end":1778680281026}},"met