{"type":"text","timestamp":1778684193379,"sessionID":"ses_1de299a6dffe1pcmWSeCkDXmvB","part":{"id":"prt_e21d6e15c001YKIzNCTDXZHKRD","messageID":"msg_e21d69185001ZXRuEyv8ZB2qyB","sessionID":"ses_1de299a6dffe1pcmWSeCkDXmvB","type":"text","text":"The structural history rules out three high-risk directions for this slot: multicycle M side unit, ready-load bypass, and a full IF/ID register. The strongest remaining structural angle is a narrow store-buffer change, because it targets random dmem backpressure without adding a new ALU, branch, or fetch critical path.","time":{"start":1778684191068,"end":1778684193377},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0d2428c896db129c016a04911ee240819997cc538b14ae1f1f","phase":"commentary"}}}}
