{"type":"text","timestamp":1778684205181,"sessionID":"ses_1de299a6dffe1pcmWSeCkDXmvB","part":{"id":"prt_e21d71245001amiY1Ejg5F8rEm","messageID":"msg_e21d70a81001XYKeZvhzgV30Ea","sessionID":"ses_1de299a6dffe1pcmWSeCkDXmvB","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis file now, scoped to `cores/bench/` and using only short `rtl/...` change paths as required.","time":{"start":1778684203589,"end":1778684205179},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0d9c56d9b821cf70016a04912b7f90819987e6b2576d053c24","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778684230704,"sessionID":"ses_1de299a6dffe1pcmWSeCkDXmvB","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_ILUb1Svmni7pLjZjuiPk07wk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r4s1\n+title: \"Add RAM store buffer\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current pipeline freezes all younger work whenever a store in EX/MEM sees\n+  io_dmemReady low, even though stores do not produce a register result for the\n+  following instructions. Under the benchmark's random dmem backpressure model,\n+  CoreMark can lose cycles waiting on regular RAM stores that could instead be\n+  queued and drained in order while independent ALU/control work continues.\n+\n+  Prior structural attempts that changed the M datapath, load-use timing, or the\n+  fetch/decode boundary regressed because they lengthened hot combinational paths\n+  or inserted broad stalls. A one-entry store buffer is a narrower structural\n+  change: it targets store-only dmem stalls, keeps loads conservative, and avoids\n+  new ALU or branch critical-path logic.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry in-order store buffer for normal RAM stores only. When a\n+  non-MMIO store reaches MEM and the buffer is empty, capture its address, data,\n+  mask, and RVFI memory metadata, allow the store instruction to retire, and let\n+  the buffer continue driving dmem_wen until io_dmemReady accepts it. Stall on\n+  loads, MMIO stores, misaligned accesses, or a full buffer so observable memory\n+  order, CoreMark timing-marker writes, UART output, and RVFI retirement remain\n+  conservative.\n+\n+  This should improve iterations per cycle under random dmem stalls by removing\n+  some whole-pipeline freezes on ordinary stores. The expected Fmax risk is\n+  modest because the buffer sits beside the MEM-stage output muxes and should not\n+  add same-cycle load-data forwarding, decode prediction, or RV32M arithmetic to\n+  the critical path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"If needed, add compact metadata bits to distinguish normal RAM stores from MMIO stores and to carry store-buffer eligibility through MEM without changing RVFI-visible fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the store dmem-stall condition with conservative store-buffer flow control: stall for loads, MMIO stores, full buffer, or buffer-drain ordering hazards, but not for enqueueable RAM stores.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement a one-entry normal-RAM store buffer that captures store address/data/mask, drives dmem until accepted, preserves RVFI store metadata at retirement, and leaves MMIO/timing-marker stores unbuffered.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire store-buffer ready/full/drain status between MEM and hazard control while preserving the nret=1 top-level RVFI and bus port contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,41 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r4s1\n+title: \"Add RAM store buffer\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current pipeline freezes all younger work whenever a store in EX/MEM sees\n+  io_dmemReady low, even though stores do not produce a register result for the\n+  following instructions. Under the benchmark's random dmem backpressure model,\n+  CoreMark can lose cycles waiting on regular RAM stores that could instead be\n+  queued and drained in order while independent ALU/control work continues.\n+\n+  Prior structural attempts that changed the M datapath, load-use timing, or the\n+  fetch/decode boundary regressed because they lengthened hot combinational paths\n+  or inserted broad stalls. A one-entry store buffer is a narrower structural\n+  change: it targets store-only dmem stalls, keeps loads conservative, and avoids\n+  new ALU or branch critical-path logic.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry in-order store buffer for normal RAM stores only. When a\n+  non-MMIO store reaches MEM and the buffer is empty, capture its address, data,\n+  mask, and RVFI memory metadata, allow the store instruction to retire, and let\n+  the buffer continue driving dmem_wen until io_dmemReady accepts it. Stall on\n+  loads, MMIO stores, misaligned accesses, or a full buffer so observable memory\n+  order, CoreMark timing-marker writes, UART output, and RVFI retirement remain\n+  conservative.\n+\n+  This should improve iterations per cycle under random dmem stalls by removing\n+  some whole-pipeline freezes on ordinary stores. The expected Fmax risk is\n+  modest because the buffer sits beside the MEM-stage output muxes and should not\n+  add same-cycle load-data forwarding, decode prediction, or RV32M arithmetic to\n+  the critical path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"If needed, add compact metadata bits to distinguish normal RAM stores from MMIO stores and to carry store-buffer eligibility through MEM without changing RVFI-visible fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the store dmem-stall condition with conservative store-buffer flow control: stall for loads, MMIO stores, full buffer, or buffer-drain ordering hazards, but not for enqueueable RAM stores.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement a one-entry normal-RAM store buffer that captures store address/data/mask, drives dmem until accepted, preserves RVFI store metadata at retirement, and leaves MMIO/timing-marker stores unbuffered.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire store-buffer ready/full/drain status between MEM and hazard control while preserving the nret=1 top-level RVFI and bus port contract.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,41 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r4s1\n+title: \"Add RAM store buffer\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current pipeline freezes all younger work whenever a store in EX/MEM sees\n+  io_dmemReady low, even though stores do not produce a register result for the\n+  following instructions. Under the benchmark's random dmem backpressure model,\n+  CoreMark can lose cycles waiting on regular RAM stores that could instead be\n+  queued and drained in order while independent ALU/control work continues.\n+\n+  Prior structural attempts that changed the M datapath, load-use timing, or the\n+  fetch/decode boundary regressed because they lengthened hot combinational paths\n+  or inserted broad stalls. A one-entry store buffer is a narrower structural\n+  change: it targets store-only dmem stalls, keeps loads conservative, and avoids\n+  new ALU or branch critical-path logic.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry in-order store buffer for normal RAM stores only. When a\n+  non-MMIO store reaches MEM and the buffer is empty, capture its address, data,\n+  mask, and RVFI memory metadata, allow the store instruction to retire, and let\n+  the buffer continue driving dmem_wen until io_dmemReady accepts it. Stall on\n+  loads, MMIO stores, misaligned accesses, or a full buffer so observable memory\n+  order, CoreMark timing-marker writes, UART output, and RVFI retirement remain\n+  conservative.\n+\n+  This should improve iterations per cycle under random dmem stalls by removing\n+  some whole-pipeline freezes on ordinary stores. The expected Fmax risk is\n+  modest because the buffer sits beside the MEM-stage output muxes and should not\n+  add same-cycle load-data forwarding, decode prediction, or RV32M arithmetic to\n+  the critical path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"If needed, add compact metadata bits to distinguish normal RAM stores from MMIO stores and to carry store-buffer eligibility through MEM without changing RVFI-visible fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the store dmem-stall condition with conservative store-buffer flow control: stall for loads, MMIO stores, full buffer, or buffer-drain ordering hazards, but not for enqueueable RAM stores.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement a one-entry normal-RAM store buffer that captures store address/data/mask, drives dmem until accepted, preserves RVFI store metadata at retirement, and leaves MMIO/timing-marker stores unbuffered.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire store-buffer ready/full/drain status between MEM and hazard control while preserving the nret=1 top-level RVFI and bus port contract.\"\n","additions":41,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778684230699,"end":1778684230703}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d9c56d9b821cf70016a04912d140c81998940864472bdaaa8"}},"id":"prt_e21d7187d001IMRQTJ7mB5ApYe","sessionID":"ses_1de299a6dffe1pcmWSeCkDXmvB","messageID":"msg_e21d70a81001XYKeZvhzgV30Ea"}}
