{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778686870896,"sessionID":"ses_1de018c10ffeppRLXYZHQQLPcT","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_GZf3yuUJ013cacXVMEqkR4Kl","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r5s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r5s1\n+title: \"Precompute PC targets in decode\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage resolves branches and jumps while also running the ALU,\n+  forwarding muxes, branch comparators, and RVFI next-PC construction. Prior\n+  structural attempts that added pipeline latency, broad stalls, or early\n+  front-end redirects regressed, so the next structural experiment should be a\n+  pure retiming that shortens EX without changing prediction policy or IPC.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Compute PC+4 and the PC-relative target PC+imm in ID and store them in the\n+  existing ID/EX pipeline register. EX can then use the precomputed PC+imm for\n+  conditional branch targets, JAL targets, and AUIPC results, and use the\n+  precomputed PC+4 for fall-through, JAL/JALR link data, and RVFI pc_wdata.\n+\n+  This removes duplicated 32-bit PC adders from the EX control path and lowers\n+  fanout around branch/jump resolution while preserving the same five-stage\n+  timing, load-use behavior, RVFI order, and single-channel nret=1 contract.\n+  Unlike the failed decode-prediction attempts, the ID-side target add feeds\n+  only a register and never drives the fetch PC in the same cycle, so it should\n+  avoid creating a new imem_data-to-PC critical loop.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Extend id_ex_t with registered pc_plus4 and pc_imm_target fields used by EX for branch, JAL, AUIPC, and RVFI next-PC construction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute pc+4 and pc+imm from the fetched PC and decoded immediate, then latch those values alongside the existing ID/EX payload.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace EX-stage pc+4 and pc+imm adders for branch/JAL/AUIPC paths with the registered ID/EX precomputed values, keeping JALR rs1+imm resolution in EX.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r5s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r5s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r5s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r5s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,31 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r5s1\n+title: \"Precompute PC targets in decode\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage resolves branches and jumps while also running the ALU,\n+  forwarding muxes, branch comparators, and RVFI next-PC construction. Prior\n+  structural attempts that added pipeline latency, broad stalls, or early\n+  front-end redirects regressed, so the next structural experiment should be a\n+  pure retiming that shortens EX without changing prediction policy or IPC.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Compute PC+4 and the PC-relative target PC+imm in ID and store them in the\n+  existing ID/EX pipeline register. EX can then use the precomputed PC+imm for\n+  conditional branch targets, JAL targets, and AUIPC results, and use the\n+  precomputed PC+4 for fall-through, JAL/JALR link data, and RVFI pc_wdata.\n+\n+  This removes duplicated 32-bit PC adders from the EX control path and lowers\n+  fanout around branch/jump resolution while preserving the same five-stage\n+  timing, load-use behavior, RVFI order, and single-