{"type":"text","timestamp":1778697325066,"sessionID":"ses_1dd613949ffegrkxoj8kow4p5Y","part":{"id":"prt_e229f47d1001g8M4HGmMUU0Ycb","messageID":"msg_e229eef0b001xvPUGN95VmoDKJ","sessionID":"ses_1dd613949ffegrkxoj8kow4p5Y","type":"text","text":"The log confirms most prior structural regressions came from adding front-end state, predictors, store queues, load bypassing, or broad M-unit stalls. I’m choosing a smaller structural retiming: register the writeback-selected value at the MEM/WB boundary so the WB stage and MEM/WB forwarding path become wires instead of a live mux.","time":{"start":1778697324497,"end":1778697325065},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_021f636897138f6a016a04c46c6124819994f32428b30a1c39","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778697346389,"sessionID":"ses_1dd613949ffegrkxoj8kow4p5Y","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_p2tRxWM6S18bIbhKGaVueSHa","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r9s1\n+title: \"Register writeback result\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current MEM/WB stage carries both alu_result and read_data, then the WB\n+  stage selects the final writeback value combinationally every cycle. That\n+  selected value feeds the regfile write port, MEM/WB forwarding into EX, and\n+  RVFI rd_wdata, so the small load-vs-ALU mux sits on several timing-relevant\n+  fanout paths even though its decision is already known when MEM/WB captures.\n+\n+  Prior structural attempts that added front-end state, prediction metadata,\n+  store buffering, or same-cycle load bypasses regressed by lengthening hotter\n+  paths or changing stall behavior. This is a narrower pipeline retiming that\n+  should preserve IPC exactly while shortening writeback and forwarding logic.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a registered wb_data field to the MEM/WB bundle and compute it inside\n+  mem_stage at the same time read_data is formed. For loads, wb_data captures\n+  the sign/zero-extended load data; for all other writeback instructions it\n+  captures the EX/MEM alu_result. Then simplify wb_stage so w_data is just the\n+  registered wb_data field, and keep RVFI rd_wdata using that same value.\n+\n+  This should remove the live MEM/WB mem_to_reg mux from the regfile write,\n+  forwarding, and RVFI rd_wdata fanout without adding stalls, changing branch\n+  resolution, touching memory handshakes, or affecting the nret=1 retirement\n+  contract. The expected benefit is modest Fmax improvement with no CoreMark\n+  iteration-per-cycle downside.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add a wb_data field to mem_wb_t so the selected writeback value is carried as registered pipeline metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute and capture wb_data at the MEM/WB boundary from load_data for loads or alu_result for non-load writeback instructions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the combinational mem_to_reg writeback mux with a direct assignment from the registered wb_data field.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r9s1\n+title: \"Register writeback result\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current MEM/WB stage carries both alu_result and read_data, then the WB\n+  stage selects the final writeback value combinationally every cycle. That\n+  selected value feeds the regfile write port, MEM/WB forwarding into EX, and\n+  RVFI rd_wdata, so the small load-vs-ALU mux sits on several timing-relevant\n+  fanout paths even though its decision is already known when MEM/WB captures.\n+\n+  Prior structural attempts that added front-end state, prediction metadata,\n+  store buffering, or same-cycle load bypasses regressed by lengthening hotter\n+  paths or changing stall behavior. This is a narrower pipeline retiming that\n+  should preserve IPC exactly while shortening writeback and forwarding logic.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a registered wb_data field to the MEM/WB bundle and compute it inside\n+  mem_stage at the same time read_data is formed. For loads, wb_data captures\n+  the sign/zero-extended load data; for all other writeback instructions it\n+  captures the EX/MEM alu_result. Then simplify wb_stage so w_data is just the\n+  registered wb_data field, and keep RVFI rd_wdata using that same value.\n+\n+  This should remove the live MEM/WB mem_to_reg mux from the regfile write,\n+  forwarding, and RVFI rd_wdata fanout without adding stalls, changing branch\n+  resolution, touching memory handshakes, or affecting the nret=1 retirement\n+  contract. The expected benefit is modest Fmax improvement with no CoreMark\n+  iteration-per-cycle downside.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add a wb_data field to mem_wb_t so the selected writeback value is carried as registered pipeline metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute and capture wb_data at the MEM/WB boundary from load_data for loads or alu_result for non-load writeback instructions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the combinational mem_to_reg writeback mux with a direct assignment from the registered wb_data field.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n+++ /Us