{"type":"text","timestamp":1778698242101,"sessionID":"ses_1dd532978ffepVV4EHcYuZuPaU","part":{"id":"prt_e22ad3fdf001Y9IXGG2Mv6QrLZ","messageID":"msg_e22ad0ef100194FOLWzUbUsoQn","sessionID":"ses_1dd532978ffepVV4EHcYuZuPaU","type":"text","text":"Prior predictor attempts consistently lost Fmax when prediction touched the fetch/decode critical path or carried wide predicted-PC metadata. I’m writing a narrower hypothesis that keeps prediction state registered and updates from EX, with a low confidence/low expected gain to reflect that history.","time":{"start":1778698239967,"end":1778698242101},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0d769613658f6e4a016a04c7ffd2ac8199849ec68597545598","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778698264666,"sessionID":"ses_1dd532978ffepVV4EHcYuZuPaU","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_A2OhH0rFCMciIt5P3B1BlATg","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r10s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r10s2\n+title: \"Predict only recently taken branch\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The core still pays a two-younger-instruction flush on every taken branch,\n+  but every previous predictor that decoded instructions in the fetch path,\n+  added general BTB/RAS structures, or carried wide predicted-PC metadata has\n+  regressed on Tang Nano timing. The remaining plausible predictor angle is a\n+  very small learned branch fast path that avoids imem_data-to-PC logic and\n+  avoids predicting jumps or returns.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry EX-trained conditional-branch predictor that stores only\n+  the most recently resolved taken backward branch PC and target. IF compares\n+  the registered PC against this one tag and, on a hit, selects the registered\n+  target as next_pc while tagging the fetched instruction with a one-bit\n+  predicted_taken flag. EX suppresses the normal redirect only when that same\n+  branch resolves taken; if it resolves not-taken or the instruction is not a\n+  matching branch, EX redirects to the already-registered pc_plus4 and clears\n+  the entry.\n+\n+  This is intentionally narrower than the failed loop predictor: no immediate\n+  decode in IF, no arrays or counters, no JAL/JALR/RAS prediction, and no\n+  32-bit predicted_pc_next pipeline comparison. It targets only stable CoreMark\n+  loop backedges and accepts low upside in exchange for minimal predictor cost.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add a one-bit predicted_taken field to IF/ID and ID/EX metadata without carrying a full predicted next PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add one registered branch PC tag and target learned from EX, predict only on a tag hit, and emit predicted_taken with the fetched instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Pass predicted_taken through the ID/EX register unchanged while preserving existing decode, RVFI source metadata, and stall/flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Update or clear the single-entry predictor from resolved backward conditional branches and suppress redirects only for correctly predicted taken branches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire EX predictor update signals into IF while preserving the nret=1 RVFI interface and existing hazard/redirect priorities.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r10s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r10s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r10s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r10s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,38 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r10s2\n+title: \"Predict only recently taken branch\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The core still pays a two-younger-instruction flush on every taken branch,\n+  but every previous predictor that decoded instructions in the fetch path,\n+  added general BTB/RAS structures, or carried wide predicted-PC metadata has\n+  regressed on Tang Nano timing. The remaining plausible predictor angle is a\n+  very small learned branch fast path that avoids imem_data-to-PC logic and\n+  avoids predicting jumps or returns.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry EX-trained conditional-branch predictor that stores only\n+  the most recently resolved taken backward branch PC and target. IF compares\n+  the registered PC against this one tag and, on a hit, selects the registered\n+  target as next_pc while tagging the fetched instruction with a one-bit\n+  predicted_taken flag. EX suppresses the normal redirect only when that same\n+  branch resolves taken; if it resolves not-taken or the instruction is not a\n+  matching branch, EX redirects to the already-registered pc_plus4 and clears\n+  the entry.\n+\n+  This is intentionally narrower than the failed loop predictor: no immediate\n+  decode in IF, no arrays or counters, no JAL/JALR/RAS prediction, and no\n+  32-bit predicted_pc_next pipeline comparison. It targets only stable CoreMark\n+  loop backedges and accepts low upside in exchange for minimal predictor cost.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add a one-bit predicted_taken field to IF/ID and ID/EX metadata without carrying a full predicted next PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add one registered branch PC tag and target learned from EX, predict only on a tag hit, and emit predicted_taken with the fetched instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Pass predicted_taken through the ID/EX register unchanged while preserving existing decode, RVFI source metadata, and stall/flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Update or clear the single-entry predictor from resolved backward conditional branches and suppress redirects only for correctly predicted taken branches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire EX predictor update signals into IF while preserving the nret=1 RVFI interface and existing hazard/redirect priorities.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.cl