ers, no JAL/JALR/RAS prediction, and no\n+  32-bit predicted_pc_next pipeline comparison. It targets only stable CoreMark\n+  loop backedges and accepts low upside in exchange for minimal predictor cost.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add a one-bit predicted_taken field to IF/ID and ID/EX metadata without carrying a full predicted next PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add one registered branch PC tag and target learned from EX, predict only on a tag hit, and emit predicted_taken with the fetched instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Pass predicted_taken through the ID/EX register unchanged while preserving existing decode, RVFI source metadata, and stall/flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Update or clear the single-entry predictor from resolved backward conditional branches and suppress redirects only for correctly predicted taken branches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire EX predictor update signals into IF while preserving the nret=1 RVFI interface and existing hazard/redirect priorities.\"\n","additions":38,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r10s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778698264662,"end":1778698264665}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d769613658f6e4a016a04c801e99481999c333f9ee1cecadc"}},"id":"prt_e22ad48350028jCLYq87HeThc6","sessionID":"ses_1dd532978ffepVV4EHcYuZuPaU","messageID":"msg_e22ad0ef100194FOLWzUbUsoQn"}}
