{"type":"text","timestamp":1778699161315,"sessionID":"ses_1dd453a1fffe7gmQytOon2H8N7","part":{"id":"prt_e22bb4325001g5jV8h0pys3yA0","messageID":"msg_e22baf1d7002sdbe6jrIcS43xf","sessionID":"ses_1dd453a1fffe7gmQytOon2H8N7","type":"text","text":"Prior predictor attempts mostly lost Fmax from decode-to-PC logic or mutable fetch-side metadata, and the latest broken case points to one concrete correctness issue: EX must validate against prediction metadata carried with the instruction, not live predictor state. I’m going to write a narrow predictor hypothesis that revisits the most timing-contained learned loop predictor but explicitly carries exact predicted target/tag metadata to avoid the previous pc_fwd failure.","time":{"start":1778699158309,"end":1778699161315},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_00edc764d63fc0c3016a04cb962e9c8198b1c200777a55a196","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778699184533,"sessionID":"ses_1dd453a1fffe7gmQytOon2H8N7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_6G1GW928HpczG1G26MxxIMnK","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r11s2\n+title: \"Carry exact loop prediction metadata\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The core still pays a two-instruction flush on taken loop backedges, but prior predictor attempts show that decode-time redirects, BTB arrays, JAL/JALR caches, and live predictor rechecks usually cost more timing or break RVFI pc_fwd. The least-bad predictor opportunity is still an EX-trained single-entry loop predictor, provided the predicted target used for redirect suppression is carried with the fetched instruction instead of reread from mutable predictor state.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a one-entry predictor for resolved taken backward conditional branches only. IF compares the registered fetch PC against a single registered tag and, on a hit, uses the registered target as next PC while storing predicted_valid, predicted_pc, and predicted_target in the IF/ID and ID/EX payload for that exact instruction. EX suppresses the normal taken-branch redirect only when the retiring branch's carried predicted_valid is set, the carried predicted_pc matches its PC, and the carried predicted_target exactly equals the resolved target; otherwise EX redirects to the resolved next PC and updates or clears the predictor.\n+\n+  This keeps instruction decode out of the fetch PC path, avoids arrays/counters/JAL/JALR/RAS speculation, and directly addresses the latest broken predictor lesson by never consulting live predictor state for RVFI pc_next validation. The expected upside is small but focused: recover repeated CoreMark loop-backedge penalties after warm-up with a single PC comparator, target mux, and exact per-instruction metadata.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact prediction metadata fields to IF/ID and ID/EX: predicted_valid, predicted_pc, and predicted_target for exact EX validation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a single-entry registered backward-branch target predictor, use it only on fetch PC tag hits, and attach the exact predicted PC/target metadata to the fetched instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Pipeline the carried prediction metadata into ID/EX without deriving prediction from decode-stage instruction bits or altering RVFI source metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Validate carried prediction metadata against the resolved branch next PC, suppress redirects only on exact matches, and expose resolved backward-branch updates for the predictor.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor update signals between EX and IF while preserving nret=1 RVFI ports, existing hazard behavior, and redirect priority.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,23 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r11s2\n+title: \"Carry exact loop prediction metadata\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The core still pays a two-instruction flush on taken loop backedges, but prior predictor attempts show that decode-time redirects, BTB arrays, JAL/JALR caches, and live predictor rechecks usually cost more timing or break RVFI pc_fwd. The least-bad predictor opportunity is still an EX-trained single-entry loop predictor, provided the predicted target used for redirect suppression is carried with the fetched instruction instead of reread from mutable predictor state.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a one-entry predictor for resolved taken backward conditional branches only. IF compares the registered fetch PC against a single registered tag and, on a hit, uses the registered target as next PC while storing predicted_valid, predicted_pc, and predicted_target in the IF/ID and ID/EX payload for that exact instruction. EX suppresses the normal taken-branch redirect only when the retiring branch's carried predicted_valid is set, the carried predicted_pc matches its PC, and the carried predicted_target exactly equals the resolved target; otherwise EX redirects to the resolved next PC and updates or clears the predictor.\n+\n+  This keeps instruction decode out of the fetch PC path, avoids arrays/counters/JAL/JALR/RAS speculation, and directly addresses the latest broken predictor lesson by never consulting live predictor state for RVFI pc_next validation. The expected upside is small but focused: recover repeated CoreMark loop-backedge penalties after warm-up with a single PC comparator, target mux, and exact per-instruction metadata.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact prediction metadata fields to IF/ID and ID/EX: predicted_valid, predicted_pc, and predicted_target for exact EX validation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a single-entry registered backward-branch target predictor, use it only on fetch PC tag hits, and attach the exact predicted PC/target metadata to the fetched instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Pipeline the carried prediction metadata into ID/EX without deriving prediction from decode-stage instruction bits or altering RVFI source metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Validate carried prediction metadata against the resolved branch next PC, suppress redirects only on exact matches, and expose resolved backward-branch updates for the predictor.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor update signals between EX and IF while preserving nret=1 RVFI ports, existing hazard behavior, and redirect priority.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,23 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r11s2\n+title: \"Carry exact loop prediction metadata\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The core still pays a two-instruction flush on taken loop backedges, but prior predictor attempts show that decode-time redirects, BTB arrays, JAL/JALR caches, and live predictor rechecks usually cost more timing or break RVFI pc_fwd. The least-bad predictor opportunity is still an EX-trained single-entry loop predictor, provided the predicted target used for redirect suppression is carried with the fetched instruction instead of reread from mutable predictor state.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a one-entry predictor for resolved taken backward conditional branches only. IF compares the registered fetch PC against a single registered tag and, on a hit, uses the registered target as next PC while storing predicted_valid, predicted_pc, and predicted_target in the IF/ID and ID/EX payload for that exact instruction. EX suppresses the normal taken-branch redirect only when the retiring branch's carried predicted_valid is set, the carried predicted_pc matches its PC, and the carried predicted_target exactly equals the resolved target; otherwise EX redirects to the resolved next PC and updates or clears the predictor.\n+\n+  This keeps instruction decode out of the fetch PC path, avoids arrays/counters/JAL/JALR/RAS speculation, and directly addresses the latest broken predictor lesson by never consulting live predictor state for RVFI pc_next validation. The expected upside is small but focused: recover repeated CoreMark loop-backedge penalties after warm-up with a single PC comparator, target mux, and exact per-instruction metadata.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact prediction metadata fields to IF/ID and ID/EX: predicted_valid, predicted_pc, and predicted_target for exact EX validation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a single-entry registered backward-branch target predictor, use it only on fetch PC tag hits, and attach the exact predicted PC/target metadata to the fetched instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Pipeline the carried prediction metadata into ID/EX without deriving prediction from decode-stage instruction bits or altering RVFI source metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Validate carried prediction metadata against the resolved branch next PC, suppress redirects only on exact matches, and expose resolved backward-branch updates for the predictor.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor update signals between EX and IF while preserving nret=1 RVFI ports, existing hazard behavior, and redirect priority.\"\n","additions":23,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778699184530,"end":1778699184532}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_00edc764d63fc0c3016a04cb99344c8198834430cc5ac4d945"}},"id":"prt_e22bb4ee3002L55URZvrdUpLfh","sessionID":"ses_1dd453a1fffe7gmQytOon2H8N7","messageID":"msg_e22baf1d7002sdbe6jrIcS43xf"}}
