{"type":"text","timestamp":1778701976384,"sessionID":"ses_1dd1aec5affefVRWlACOmwbImZ","part":{"id":"prt_e22e63de50015w29qqKNktfz0X","messageID":"msg_e22e5a40a0019SMdwGyWi1pItL","sessionID":"ses_1dd1aec5affefVRWlACOmwbImZ","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a delayed single-entry loop predictor hypothesis: it trades one cycle of branch penalty recovery for keeping the predictor tag compare off the same-cycle PC update path, which directly targets the main failure mode from earlier predictor attempts.","time":{"start":1778701975013,"end":1778701976382},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0ca6b3d5f47cd04f016a04d696e6b8819ab423887d3078eeed","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778702000274,"sessionID":"ses_1dd1aec5affefVRWlACOmwbImZ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_sC50o4BTlKjGe8BM1GjHXr1r","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r14s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r14s2\n+title: \"Delayed loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core still loses two younger instructions on every taken loop\n+  branch, but prior predictor attempts show that same-cycle fetch PC tag\n+  compares, decode-immediate redirects, BTB/RAS state, and redirect-cycle\n+  instruction injection usually cost more FPGA timing than they recover.\n+  A predictor experiment is still worthwhile only if it avoids adding logic to\n+  the normal imem_data-to-PC or PC-tag-hit-to-PC critical path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a one-entry delayed loop predictor trained only by resolved taken\n+  backward conditional branches. During fetch, compare the current registered\n+  PC against the learned branch PC and register the hit/target metadata, but\n+  do not use that same-cycle compare to choose the next PC. One cycle later,\n+  while the branch is in decode, use the registered hit to redirect fetch to\n+  the stored target and carry the exact predicted target with that branch into\n+  EX. EX suppresses the normal taken-branch redirect only when the carried\n+  prediction matches the resolved target; otherwise it falls back to the\n+  existing redirect and flush behavior.\n+\n+  This deliberately recovers at most one of the two taken-branch penalty\n+  cycles, but it removes the predictor tag compare from the fetch PC update\n+  cone that hurt previous one-entry loop predictors. It also avoids decode\n+  immediate generation for prediction, arrays, counters, JAL/JALR/RAS cases,\n+  and redirect-target instruction caching. The expected upside is modest, but\n+  this is the narrowest remaining predictor-only path that can improve loop\n+  IPC without recreating the known Tang Nano timing regressions.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact carried prediction fields to IF/ID and ID/EX for delayed loop hits: predicted valid and predicted target for the exact fetched branch.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a single-entry EX-trained backward-branch predictor whose PC compare result is registered for next-cycle use, then redirect fetch from that registered hit rather than the same-cycle compare.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Train the delayed predictor from resolved taken backward branches and suppress the normal branch redirect only when the carried predicted target exactly matches the resolved target.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire delayed predictor update and carried prediction metadata between IF, ID, and EX without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r14s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r14s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r14s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r14s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,40 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r14s2\n+title: \"Delayed loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core still loses two younger instructions on every taken loop\n+  branch, but prior predictor attempts show that same-cycle fetch PC tag\n+  compares, decode-immediate redirects, BTB/RAS state, and redirect-cycle\n+  instruction injection usually cost more FPGA timing than they recover.\n+  A predictor experiment is still worthwhile only if it avoids adding logic to\n+  the normal imem_data-to-PC or PC-tag-hit-to-PC critical path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a one-entry delayed loop predictor trained only by resolved taken\n+  backward conditional branches. During fetch, compare the current registered\n+  PC against the learned branch PC and register the hit/target metadata, but\n+  do not use that same-cycle compare to choose the next PC. One cycle later,\n+  while the branch is in decode, use the registered hit to redirect fetch to\n+  the stored target and carry the exact predicted target with that branch into\n+  EX. EX suppresses the normal taken-branch redirect only when the carried\n+  prediction matches the resolved target; otherwise it falls back to the\n+  existing redirect and flush behavior.\n+\n+  This deliberately recovers at most one of the two taken-branch penalty\n+  cycles, but it removes the predictor tag compare from the fetch PC update\n+  cone that hurt previous one-entry loop predictors. It also avoids decode\n+  immediate generation for prediction, arrays, counters, JAL/JALR/RAS cases,\n+  and redirect-target instruction caching. The expected upside is modest, but\n+  this is the narrowest remaining predictor-only path that can improve loop\n+  IPC without recreating the known Tang Nano timing regressions.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact carried prediction fields to IF/ID and ID/EX for delayed loop hits: predicted valid and predicted target for the exact fetched branch.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a single-entry EX-trained backward-branch predictor whose PC compare result is registered for next-cycle use, then redirect fetch from that registered hit rather than the same-cycle compare.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Train the delayed predictor from resolved taken backward branches and suppress the normal branch redirect only when the carried predicted target exactly matches the resolved target.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire delayed predictor update and carried prediction metadata between IF, ID, and EX without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r14s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r14s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r14s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r14s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r14s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,40 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r14s2\n+title: \"Delayed loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core still loses two younger instructions on every taken loop\n+  branch, but prior predictor attempts show that same-cycle fetch PC tag\n+  compares, decode-immediate redirects, BTB/RAS state, and redirect-cycle\n+  instruction injection usually cost more FPGA timing than they recover.\n+  A predictor experiment is still worthwhile only if it avoids adding logic to\n+  the normal imem_data-to-PC or PC-tag-hit-to-PC critical path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a one-entry delayed loop predictor trained only by resolved taken\n+  backward conditional branches. During fetch, compare the current registered\n+  PC against the learned branch 