l, but it may recover one bubble on hot loop backedges while keeping the proven five-stage control path and all misprediction recovery in EX.\\n\", \"exp...\n  Line 41: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r14s0\", \"title\": \"Bypass LUI around ALU\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The successful micro-optimization history for this core favors narrow datapath cleanup over new control, prediction, buffering, or memory-lane restructuring. The current EX stage already carries a decoded is_lui bit through ctrl_t, but LUI still enters the full ALU case as ALU_LUI just to return the immediate operand. That keeps one U-type-only operation in the same result mux and ALU op decode used by CoreMark's common adds, compares, branches, and load/store address calculations.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The successful micro-optimization history for this core favors narrow datapath cleanup over new control, prediction, buffering, or memory-lane restructuring. The current EX stage already carries a decoded is_lui bit through ctrl_t, but LUI still enters the full ALU case as ALU_LUI just to return the immediate operand. That keeps one U-type-only operation in the same result mux and ALU op decode used by CoreMark's common adds, compares, branches, and load/store address calculations.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Route LUI writeback in rtl/ex_stage.sv through the existing final EX/MEM result selection, the same style already used for JAL/JALR link data and AUIPC pc_imm_target, and remove ALU_LUI from rtl/alu.sv's active result case. The decoder can still set ctrl.is_lui and an otherwise harmless ALU op, but LUI's architectural result will be in.imm captured directly into ex_mem.alu_result.\\n\\nThis should slightly shrink the monolithic ALU result case and reduce ALU op decode fanout without adding state, stalls, bypasses, predictor metadata, or any RVFI-visible behavior. It is intentionally smaller than the failed AUIPC cleanup: it does not delete existing metadata or change operand-a routing for all instructions, only moves one already-decoded U-type result out of the common ALU datapath.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 1, \"confidence\": \"low\"}, \"chan...\n  Line 42: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r14s1\", \"title\": \"Predecode branch compare class\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The current EX stage still decodes the branch comparison class from branch_op\\nwhile it is also resolving forwarded operands, ALU output, redirect, and RVFI\\npc_next. Prior front-end prediction and target-injection attempts regressed\\nbecause they added fetch-PC muxing or mutable prediction metadata, while the\\nsuccessful structural win was a pure ID-to-EX retiming of PC target values.\\n\\nA similarly narrow retiming can move branch comparator control preparation out\\nof the EX hot path without changing when branches resolve, adding pipeline\\nlatency, or touching memory/M-extension behavior.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current EX stage still decodes the branch comparison class from branch_op\\nwhile it is also resolving forwarded operands, ALU output, redirect, and RVFI\\npc_next. Prior front-end prediction and target-injection attempts regressed\\nbecause they added fetch-PC muxing or mutable prediction metadata, while the\\nsuccessful structural win was a pure ID-to-EX retiming of PC target values.\\n\\nA similarly narrow retiming can move branch comparator control preparation out\\nof the EX hot path without changing when branches resolve, adding pipeline\\nlatency, or touching memory/M-extension behavior.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add compact decoded branch-compare control bits to the ID/EX pipeline payload,\\nderived from the already-decoded branch_op in ID. EX should use those registered\\nbits to select equality, signed-less-than, or unsigned-less-than comparison and\\na final invert flag, instead of carrying the raw funct3-style branch_op through\\na full case statement on the EX redirect path.\\n\\nThis preserves the five-stage pipeline, single nret=1 retirement contract,\\nexisting forwarding operands, misalignment trap behavior, and EX-stage branch\\nresolution point. The expected gain is Fmax from simplifying the branch\\ncondition/control cone in EX; IP...\n  Line 43: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r14s2\", \"title\": \"Delayed loop predictor\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The current core still loses two younger instructions on every taken loop\\nbranch, but prior predictor attempts show that same-cycle fetch PC tag\\ncompares, decode-immediate redirects, BTB/RAS state, and redirect-cycle\\ninstruction injection usually cost more FPGA timing than they recover.\\nA predictor experiment is still worthwhile only if it avoids adding logic to\\nthe normal imem_data-to-PC or PC-tag-hit-to-PC critical path.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current core still loses two younger instructions on every taken loop\\nbranch, but prior predictor attempts show that same-cycle fetch PC tag\\ncompares, decode-immediate redirects, BTB/RAS state, and redirect-cycle\\ninstruction injection usually cost more FPGA timing than they recover.\\nA predictor experiment is still worthwhile only if it avoids adding logic to\\nthe normal imem_data-to-PC or PC-tag-hit-to-PC critical path.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a one-entry delayed loop predictor trained only by resolved taken\\nbackward conditional branches. During fetch, compare the current registered\\nPC against the learned branch PC and register the hit/target metadata, but\\ndo not use that same-cycle compare to choose the next PC. One cycle later,\\nwhile the branch is in decode, use the registered hit to redirect fetch to\\nthe stored target and carry the exact predicted target with that branch into\\nEX. EX suppresses the normal taken-branch redirect only when the carried\\nprediction matches the resolved target; otherwise it falls back to the\\nexisting redirect and flush behavior.\\n\\nThis deliberately recovers at most one of the two taken-branch penalty\\ncycles, but it removes the predictor tag compare from the fetch PC update\\ncone that hurt previous one-entry loop predictors. It also avoids decode\\nimmediate generation for prediction, arrays, counters, JAL/JALR/RAS cases,\\nand redirect-target instruction cachi...","metadata":{"matches":29,"truncated":false},"title":"category: predictor|predictor|Predict|branch prediction|BTB|RAS|loop predictor|redirect","time":{"start":1778703051369,"end":1778703051380}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0632469d9c874242016a04dacb3c58819a99ad8d3cedb5e0f9"}},"id":"prt_e22f6aa640013SFMu0Mv7OkBXh","sessionID":"ses_1dd0982e5ffewX9K3S6ymzWTPv","messageID":"msg_e22f67d570015kltoCwPOuaNXv"}}
