{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778678090504,"sessionID":"ses_1de86d64dffe21MXEWfE5ZjBOh","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_JZ4sKbBLGPX24bX3RHVzEbm9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r1s2\n+title: \"Add tiny backward-branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage core resolves every conditional branch in EX and then\n+  flushes two younger wrong-path instructions on taken branches. CoreMark has\n+  many small loop backedges, so the static not-taken policy wastes cycles on the\n+  hottest control-flow pattern while also exposing random instruction stalls to\n+  extra refetch work.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a minimal static predictor in fetch/decode that predicts backward\n+  conditional branches taken and redirects the PC to the decoded B-immediate\n+  target before EX. Carry predicted-next-PC metadata through ID/EX so EX can\n+  distinguish correct predictions from mispredictions, only flushing on actual\n+  mismatches. This should remove most taken-loop branch penalties with very low\n+  LUT cost and little Fmax risk compared with a dynamic BHT/BTB.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Extend the IF/ID and ID/EX bundles with predicted PC and predicted-taken metadata for branch recovery.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Accept an early decode redirect for backward branches and report the predicted next PC alongside the fetched instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect backward conditional branches from the fetched instruction, compute the B-immediate target, and pass prediction metadata into EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare the predicted next PC against the resolved branch or jump next PC and redirect only on prediction mismatch.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire early branch prediction signals between ID and IF while preserving the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,30 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r1s2\n+title: \"Add tiny backward-branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage core resolves every conditional branch in EX and then\n+  flushes two younger wrong-path instructions on taken branches. CoreMark has\n+  many small loop backedges, so the static not-taken policy wastes cycles on the\n+  hottest control-flow pattern while also exposing random instruction stalls to\n+  extra refetch work.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a minimal static predictor in fetch/decode that predicts backward\n+  conditional branches taken and redirects the PC to the decoded B-immediate\n+  target before EX. Carry predicted-next-PC metadata through ID/EX so EX can\n+  distinguish correct predictions from mispredictions, only flushing on actual\n+  mismatches. This should remove most taken-loop branch penalties with very low\n+  LUT cost and little Fmax risk compared with a dynamic BHT/BTB.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    de