{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778679200577,"sessionID":"ses_1de762594ffebTVSf2tMVRGvNU","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_4XGI7fwDg434BcnxSFf6R30B","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r2s2\n+title: \"Correct ID backward-branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage core pays a two-instruction flush penalty on every taken conditional branch because branches resolve in EX and fetch is effectively static not-taken. CoreMark's inner loops should contain frequent backward taken branches, so recovering even part of that penalty can improve iterations per cycle without touching the already successful M-extension ALU optimization.\n+\n+  The previous predictor attempt identified the right low-cost direction but failed because EX compared against IF fall-through metadata rather than the branch's decoded target, so nominally correct backward predictions still looked wrong. A corrected metadata path is the most promising predictor-only follow-up.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a minimal static predictor that operates after decode: when ID sees a valid conditional branch with a negative B-immediate, redirect fetch to the decoded branch target and mark that branch with predicted_taken and predicted_pc_next in the ID/EX payload. EX then computes the resolved next PC for branches and jumps and redirects only when resolved_pc_next differs from the carried predicted_pc_next.\n+\n+  This keeps the predictor tiny: no BHT, no BTB, no tags, and no speculative history state. Forward progress and RVFI ordering remain anchored at the existing MEM/WB retirement point, while correct backward loop predictions avoid fetching and later flushing the two fall-through instructions behind each taken loop branch.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Extend IF/ID and ID/EX bundles with predicted_taken and predicted_pc_next fields so each branch carries its own prediction metadata to EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire an ID-stage early redirect to IF alongside the existing EX redirect, preserving EX redirect priority for misprediction recovery.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Accept an early predicted redirect target from ID and update the PC to that target when no EX redirect overrides it.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Decode negative conditional B-immediates, compute the exact branch target, request the early redirect, and latch prediction metadata with the branch.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Resolve branch and jump next PC, compare it with predicted_pc_next, and assert redirect only on a real prediction mismatch or unpredicted jump.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Treat an ID predicted redirect like a front-end flush event while keeping load-use and dmem-stall precedence intact.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r2s2\n+title: \"Correct ID backward-branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage co