{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778680288614,"sessionID":"ses_1de65a0efffethTDFbccQ3rAe5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_mSb7jj4JYjVKskJAi0BivFA0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r3s2\n+title: \"Add tiny fetch BTB predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core still resolves all branches and jumps in EX, so every taken\n+  control transfer pays a two-younger-instruction flush. Prior predictor\n+  attempts showed that decode-time backward prediction is risky on this FPGA\n+  because the imem_data-to-decode-to-target-add path can become part of the\n+  fetch critical path. A fetch-PC-indexed BTB avoids that failed path while\n+  still targeting CoreMark's hot loop backedges and repeated call/return-like\n+  JAL/JALR targets.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a very small direct-mapped BTB in the fetch stage, indexed only by the\n+  registered PC and updated from EX when a branch or jump resolves. Each entry\n+  stores valid, tag, target, and a one-bit or two-bit taken confidence bit;\n+  fetch predicts to the stored target only on a tag hit, otherwise it keeps the\n+  existing pc+4 behavior. Carry predicted_pc_next through IF/ID and ID/EX so EX\n+  redirects only when the resolved next PC differs from the prediction, and\n+  update or allocate entries for taken branches/JAL/JALR while weakening or\n+  clearing entries on not-taken branches.\n+\n+  This is the most promising predictor-only follow-up because it removes the\n+  known ID predictor critical path, learns actual targets instead of relying on\n+  a static backward heuristic, and should recover taken-control IPC on stable\n+  CoreMark loops with modest LUT/FF cost.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles so EX can compare prediction versus resolved control flow.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement a tiny PC-indexed direct-mapped BTB lookup in fetch and update entries from EX-resolved branch/jump outcomes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Propagate predicted next-PC metadata from IF/ID into ID/EX without adding decode-time target prediction logic.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Resolve the actual next PC for branches and jumps, signal mispredictions by comparing against predicted next PC, and provide BTB update information.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire EX prediction-resolution and BTB-update signals between execute and fetch while preserving the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,39 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r3s2\n+title: \"Add tiny fetch BTB predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core still resolves all branches and jumps in EX, so every taken\n+  control transfer pays a two-younger-instruction flush. Prior predictor\n+  attempts showed that decode-time backward prediction is risky on this FPGA\n+  because the imem_data-to-decode-to-target-add path can become part of the\n+  fetch critical