{"type":"text","timestamp":1778686833097,"sessionID":"ses_1de018b45ffekdfZ3EdDJoPFDU","part":{"id":"prt_e21ff2a99001PinSFqKL80q7tA","messageID":"msg_e21ff1e23001L6rlMpFAdT8YdT","sessionID":"ses_1de018b45ffekdfZ3EdDJoPFDU","type":"text","text":"I’ll write the hypothesis as a single focused predictor experiment: a one-entry JALR/return target cache with scalar state, not a general BTB or decode-time branch predictor.","time":{"start":1778686831257,"end":1778686833095},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0155184904aceef6016a049b6f21b08199b4c96a670d2f58bf","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778686855920,"sessionID":"ses_1de018b45ffekdfZ3EdDJoPFDU","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_X0tKLMUlsz2zpgXSJK3xvnBb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r5s2\n+title: \"One-entry JALR return predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The existing core resolves JALR in EX, so every function return pays the same two-younger-instruction flush as a taken branch. Prior predictor attempts lost fitness or broke formal because they added decode-time target generation on the imem critical path or introduced a general mutable BTB array. A much narrower predictor can target repeated return PCs without touching conditional branches or adding a broad fetch/decode target path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single scalar JALR target cache in fetch, updated only when EX resolves a legal JALR. The cache stores one valid bit, one PC tag, and one resolved target; when the current fetch PC matches the tag, IF predicts the cached target as the next PC and carries predicted_pc_next metadata through ID/EX. EX compares the resolved next PC against the carried prediction and redirects only on mismatch, while all branches, JAL, and cache misses keep the current pc+4/static-not-taken behavior.\n+\n+  This is deliberately smaller than the failed BTB attempt: no predictor array, no counters, no conditional-branch update policy, and no imem_data-to-immediate-to-PC combinational redirect. It should recover recurring CoreMark return penalties after warm-up with limited LUT/FF cost and lower formal risk than a general fetch BTB.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted_pc_next metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles so EX can distinguish correct JALR target-cache predictions from misses or mispredictions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add one-entry scalar JALR target-cache state, predict next PC from a tag match, and update the cache from EX-resolved JALR PCs and targets.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Pass fetch prediction metadata into the ID/EX register without adding decode-time target generation or branch prediction logic.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose resolved JALR update information and suppress redirects when the carried predicted_pc_next already matches the resolved jump target.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire EX JALR update signals back to IF and preserve the single-channel RVFI retirement contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,23 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r5s2\n+title: \"One-entry JALR return predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The existing core resolves JALR in EX, so every function return pays the same two-younger-instruction flush as a taken branch. Prior predictor attempts lost fitness or broke formal because they added decode-time target generation on the imem critical path or introduced a general mutable BTB array. A much narrower predictor can target repeated return PCs without touching conditional branches or adding a broad fetch/decode target path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single scalar JALR target cache in fetch, updated only when EX resolves a legal JALR. The cache stores one valid bit, one PC tag, and one resolved target; when the current fetch PC matches the tag, IF predicts the cached target as the next PC and carries predicted_pc_next metadata through ID/EX. EX compares the resolved next PC against the carried prediction and redirects only on mismatch, while all branches, JAL, and cache misses keep the current pc+4/static-not-taken behavior.\n+\n+  This is deliberately smaller than the failed BTB attempt: no predictor array, no counters, no conditional-branch update policy, and no imem_data-to-immediate-to-PC combinational redirect. It should recover recurring CoreMark return penalties after warm-up with limited LUT/FF cost and lower formal risk than a general fetch BTB.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted_pc_next metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles so EX can distinguish correct JALR target-cache predictions from misses or mispredictions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add one-entry scalar JALR target-cache state, predict next PC from a tag match, and update the cache from EX-resolved JALR PCs and targets.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Pass fetch prediction metadata into the ID/EX register without adding decode-time target generation or branch prediction logic.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose resolved JALR update information and suppress redirects when the carried predicted_pc_next already matches the resolved jump target.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire EX JALR update signals back to IF and preserve the single-channel RVFI retirement contract.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-2