{"type":"text","timestamp":1778689232351,"sessionID":"ses_1dddcacc2ffeVY4HZdCLfHRI4k","part":{"id":"prt_e2223c6c7001dYwNN7M0FOOlCQ","messageID":"msg_e2223c01600132tesLz2bKrT8J","sessionID":"ses_1dddcacc2ffeVY4HZdCLfHRI4k","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the YAML now with short `rtl/...` paths and `category: predictor`, avoiding any edits outside `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses`.","time":{"start":1778689230535,"end":1778689232350},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0c3b70e9fcd9250e016a04a4ce702c819aaaa0c139b7688da4","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778689254584,"sessionID":"ses_1dddcacc2ffeVY4HZdCLfHRI4k","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_aOZDDusa6K9Z5ZvcL3IAR2il","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r6s2\n+title: \"Add loop-target prefetch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The existing core still pays a taken-control penalty, but prior predictor\n+  attempts show that decode-time redirects and mutable BTB-style PC metadata\n+  can lose more Fmax or formal convergence than they recover in IPC. CoreMark\n+  nevertheless has tight repeated loops, and the random imem backpressure model\n+  makes avoiding wrong-path fetch work valuable if the predictor can stay off\n+  the critical PC-update path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny one-entry loop-target prefetch predictor that learns only resolved\n+  taken backward conditional branches in EX, storing the branch PC and target in\n+  flops. Fetch keeps the architecturally visible PC policy unchanged until a\n+  registered PC tag hit is observed, then uses the stored target as the next PC\n+  and carries a predicted_pc_next value with that fetched instruction so EX can\n+  suppress the normal redirect only when the resolved next PC exactly matches.\n+\n+  This is deliberately narrower than the failed BTB and decode predictors: no\n+  predictor array, no instruction-decode-to-PC immediate path, no JAL/JALR\n+  target speculation, and no change to branch condition resolution. It should\n+  recover the hottest loop backedge penalties after warm-up while limiting Fmax\n+  risk to a single PC comparator and target mux driven by registered predictor\n+  state.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact predicted_pc_next metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX payloads so EX can validate a fetch-side loop prediction without changing RVFI ordering.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a one-entry registered backward-branch target predictor updated from EX and use only registered PC/tag hits to choose the next fetch PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Emit resolved taken-backward branch update information and redirect only when the carried predicted next PC differs from the resolved next PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor update and predicted-next-PC signals between IF and EX while preserving the nret=1 top-level IO contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r6s2\n+title: \"Add loop-target prefetch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The existing core still pays a taken-control penalty, but prior predictor\n+  attempts show that decode-time redirects and mutable BTB-style PC metadata\n+  can lose more Fmax or formal convergence than they recover in IPC. CoreMark\n+  nevertheless has tight repeated loops, and the random imem backpressure model\n+  makes avoiding wrong-path fetch work valuable if the predictor can stay off\n+  the critical PC-update path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny one-entry loop-target prefetch predictor that learns only resolved\n+  taken backward conditional branches in EX, storing the branch PC and target in\n+  flops. Fetch keeps the architecturally visible PC policy unchanged until a\n+  registered PC tag hit is observed, then uses the stored target as the next PC\n+  and carries a predicted_pc_next value with that fetched instruction so EX can\n+  suppress the normal redirect only when the resolved next PC exactly matches.\n+\n+  This is deliberately narrower than the failed BTB and decode predictors: no\n+  predictor array, no instruction-decode-to-PC immediate path, no JAL/JALR\n+  target speculation, and no change to branch condition resolution. It should\n+  recover the hottest loop backedge penalties after warm-up while limiting Fmax\n+  risk to a single PC comparator and target mux driven by registered predictor\n+  state.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact predicted_pc_next metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX payloads so EX can validate a fetch-side loop prediction without changing RVFI ordering.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a one-entry registered backward-branch target predictor updated from EX and use only registered PC/tag hits to choose the next fetch PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Emit resolved taken-backward branch update information and redirect only when the carried predicted next PC differs from the resolved next PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor update and predicted-next-PC signals between IF and EX while preserving the nret=1 top-level IO contract.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament