{"type":"text","timestamp":1778696117348,"sessionID":"ses_1dd739f09ffehNCbWn7O3aErGE","part":{"id":"prt_e228cd07f0019QT2GzUyV5EEPD","messageID":"msg_e228c8c18001u0U5EMacBo1ydJ","sessionID":"ses_1dd739f09ffehNCbWn7O3aErGE","type":"text","text":"Prior predictor attempts mainly failed from fetch critical-path cost, dynamic metadata/formal complexity, or too little benefit from JAL/JALR/loop target caches. I’m going to make the new predictor hypothesis deliberately narrower: a decode-only static hint that does not drive the fetch PC, but changes front-end flush policy for predicted-not-taken forward branches to avoid killing useful fall-through work on correctly not-taken branches.","time":{"start":1778696114303,"end":1778696117347},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_05e2cd0b21b2987d016a04bfb23314819aa98b36d6bfed62d8","phase":"commentary"}}}}
