{"type":"text","timestamp":1778696144565,"sessionID":"ses_1dd739f09ffehNCbWn7O3aErGE","part":{"id":"prt_e228d3d45001Naay6Mw4YmQzDJ","messageID":"msg_e228d34fe001SLaar4UmKwDqHs","sessionID":"ses_1dd739f09ffehNCbWn7O3aErGE","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis as a small return-address predictor: decode predicts only canonical `JALR x0, 0(ra)` returns from a tiny RAS target, avoiding the immediate-add and BTB-array costs that hurt prior predictor attempts.","time":{"start":1778696142149,"end":1778696144565},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0c3bb2be18a13ada016a04bfce0d2c8198a937410ad1794981","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778696170423,"sessionID":"ses_1dd739f09ffehNCbWn7O3aErGE","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_WQay6VRHO31Vkq4OMxcNY63O","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r8s2\n+title: \"Predict returns with tiny RAS\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The existing core still resolves every JALR in EX, so function returns pay the normal taken-control flush penalty. Prior predictor attempts lost fitness when they added decode-time immediate target generation, fetch-side BTB/tag arrays, or broad predicted-PC metadata for many control-flow classes. CoreMark still has repeated call/return structure, so a narrower return-only predictor may recover useful IPC with less timing cost than general branch or JAL target prediction.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny return-address stack predictor for canonical returns only. When EX retires or resolves a legal JAL that writes x1 or x5, push the already-available pc_plus4 link address into a 2-entry RAS; when decode sees a valid JALR with rs1=x1 or x5, rd=x0, and imm=0, redirect fetch to the registered RAS top one cycle before EX would otherwise resolve it. Carry predicted_pc_next and predicted_valid for that instruction through ID/EX, and in EX suppress the normal JALR redirect only if the computed target exactly matches the carried prediction; otherwise redirect to the resolved target and repair or invalidate the RAS entry.\n+\n+  This differs from the failed JAL decode predictor because there is no imem_data-to-J-immediate-adder-to-PC path, and differs from the failed JALR target cache because returns use call-pushed link addresses rather than a fetch PC target cache. The critical added decode path is only opcode/rd/rs1/imm-zero qualification plus a mux selecting a registered RAS top, so the Fmax risk should be lower while still targeting frequent CoreMark returns.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact predicted_pc_next and predicted_valid fields to ID/EX so return predictions can be validated at EX without changing RVFI retirement width.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Accept a decode-stage return prediction redirect target, update PC from it with lower priority than EX redirects, and emit bubbles only on actual redirect conflicts.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect canonical return-form JALR instructions and request an early redirect to the registered RAS top while carrying prediction metadata with the decoded instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Validate predicted JALR next PCs against the resolved target, suppress matching redirects, and expose call/return update information for the RAS.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate the tiny 2-entry RAS state, wire decode prediction requests and EX validation/update signals, and preserve existing nret=1 RVFI port behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,23 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r8s2\n+title: \"Predict returns with tiny RAS\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivatio